title: saucepan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt shortening; add sugar and vanilla. Stir well, then add eggs.
Stir, then add remaining dry ingredients.
Use nuts of your choice.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
The secret is to be sure and shake the pan every 5 minutes for a delicious chewy brownie.

title: apple cake
directions: Put eggs and sugar in a bowl and with the electric mixer at medium speed, mix them thoroughly.
Then add milk, oil, flour and baking soda and mix again.
Last add apples and walnuts (chopped) and stir them into the mixture.
Prepare your cake mold by greasing.
Pour the mixture into the mold.
Bake it at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Wait until it becomes cold to take it out of the cake mold.

title: pineapple and peach cobbler
directions: Put crushed pineapple in oblong dish. Put peaches on top of pineapple. Crumble dry cake mix over fruit. Put coarsely chopped pecans on top. Sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar on top. Melt 1/4 pound butter over top. Heat oven to 350°. Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Eat while warm with ice cream.

title: jan's famous baked beans
directions: Cook the bacon.
Lay aside on paper towels.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and simmer until brown sugar is melted. Crumble the bacon in small pieces and add.
Simmer until the bacon is warm.
Do not boil!!!
Can be frozen.
You can also add any of your favorite ingredients (i.e.
onions).

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Beat egg yolks, brown sugar and vegetable oil together until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients, blend well and place scoops on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: squash pickles
directions: Place squash in salted water to cover and let stand 1 hour. Drain well and set aside.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and boil gently for 5 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Screw metal bans on tightly.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: With hand electric mixer, whip together whipped topping, cold milk, vanilla, cream cheese and confectioners sugar, then pour into cool pie shell.
Top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate for 3 hours or more.

title: fried chicken in oven
directions: Dip chicken in batter of yogurt, egg, oil and thyme.
Fully cover all sides.
Dip chicken in bread crumbs (all sides).
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until browned.
Tastes like fried chicken.
Serves 4.

title: cream of fresh tomato soup
directions: In saucepan, simmer tomatoes, onion and bay leaf.
Add sugar, salt and pepper for 10 minutes.
Run through sieve and set aside. In saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and cook about 2 minutes.
Add milk at once.
Cook; stirring until thick, add salt and pepper to white sauce.
Slowly stir in tomato mixture.
Garnish with green onion if you wish and basil.
Yields 4 cups.

title: hospitality pie
directions: Toast coconut and almonds in melted margarine until brown (325°, about 10 minutes); cool.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Using 1/2 of the cream cheese mixture, divide equally between the 3 crusts.
Top with 1/2 of the coconut/almonds.
Drizzle 1/2 butterscotch topping over the 3 crusts.
Repeat for second layer.
Freeze.
Makes 3 delicious pies!

title: glorious strawberry pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shells.
Spread cream cheese over bottom of shells.
Arrange strawberries over these.
Mix sugar, cold water, cornstarch, syrup, butter and salt.
Bring to boil.
Cook until thick (5 to 7 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in jello while hot.
Chill until almost congealed before pouring over strawberries.
When cool, pour over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: cottage pie
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; boil 20 minutes.
Peel and slice onions and carrots.
Fry meat, onions and carrots until meat is brown and onions and carrots are soft.
Add a little water, salt, pepper and herbs.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Mash potatoes and spread on top of casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese is brown.

title: bill's chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook chocolate and milk over low heat, stirring until mixture blends.
Add sugar, corn syrup and salt into mixture.
Place over moderate heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat (wiping sugar crystals from side of pan as necessary) until soft ball stage (236° to 238°).

title: sweet italian spaghetti
directions: Bring 5 qts. water to a boil, add pasta and stir.
Boil 10 minutes or to desired tenderness stirring occasionally. Drain, rinse, add butter, stir until butter melts and set aside.
Boil Dino Sausages approx. 20 minutes.
Peel skin and set aside.
Brown and season (to your preference) ground turkey or beef. Drain and simmer, adding Ragu sauce, McCormick sauce mix and water. Cut/chop Dino Sausages into 1/2 inch slices.
Add Dino Sausages to spaghetti sauce and simmer for additional 5 minutes.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with ice cream sandwiches (may have to cut some to make a good fit).
Spread Cool Whip on top of sandwiches.
Drizzle topping on top of Cool Whip. Freeze 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Brown ground beef and onion together. Add other ingredients in a Dutch oven or slow cooker.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: avocado mousse with raw mushroom salad
directions: Pare and pit avocados; sprinkle each with lemon juice.
Puree in blender or food processor; transfer to large bowl.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add salt, pepper and the pepper sauce.
Combine gelatin and 1/4 cup cold water in small bowl.
Place bowl over hot water, stir until gelatin is dissolved. Mix bouillon mixture and gelatin, stir into pureed avocado.
Beat cream until it forms stiff peaks; fold into avocado mixture; stir in mayonnaise.
Pour into 7-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate, covered, until firm, 6 hours or overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, but not more than 30 minutes.

title: wet burritos
directions: Brown meat, salt, pepper, garlic powder and cumin; drain fat. On each tortilla shell, spread beans, meat, lettuce and tomato. Divide amounts equally in fourths.
Fold over sides and roll up. Place in ovenproof dish.
Pour over sauce; sprinkle with cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts or put in microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Heat remaining sauce and pour over.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
In medium bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, seasoned salt, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce until blended. Stir in crabmeat.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving to blend flavors.
Serve cold with potato chips or corn chips for dipping.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1/2 cup cheese and put in casserole dish.
Put last 1/2 cup cheese on top when about done. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients together and drop on greased cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove with spatula and place on wax paper to cool.
Makes 100.

title: bread sticks
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Make a dough of flour, sugar and milk.
Roll out dough into a 3 x 9-inch shape.
Put into baking dish.
Cut slightly down middle.
Cut crosswise to make indentions for sections.
Spread margarine on top and in cracks. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 475°.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan (lightly greased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until gelatin starts to congeal.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into 2-inch deep 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding; pour over bread crumbs.
Cool; add melted butter, sugar, eggs, salt, raisins and cinnamon or nutmeg. Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm with or without sauce or cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: herb bread
directions: Cut bread.
Combine oleo and herbs. Spread between each cut slice of bread. Wrap bread loosely in foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper; grease and flour paper.
Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin; mix well.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon which have been mixed together.
Spread in pan; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle a tea towel or cheesecloth with powdered sugar.
Turn cake upside-down onto towel.
Remove wax paper and roll up in towel and cool.
Unroll; spread with filling and re-roll.
Refrigerate.

title: terry's bacon poles
directions: Cut bacon in half lengthwise.
Coat one side with Parmesan cheese.
Wrap the bacon in a spiral, cheese side next to stick. Lay on paper towel.
Put 10 on a plate.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes.
Roll again in cheese.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to rolling boil. Cool. Add remaining ingredients and stir. Freeze in gallon container.
Thaw 1 hour before serving.
Mix with 2 large bottles of ginger ale.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper; blend until smooth.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Top with mushrooms, tomatoes, broccoli, green pepper and onions.
Cut into appetizer size pieces.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 60 appetizers.

title: potatoes jurissienne
directions: Layer potatoes as for scalloped potatoes.
On each layer put generous pats of butter, salt, pepper and Swiss cheese and repeat for each layer.
On top drizzle with small container of heavy whipping cream.
Simmer on top of stove until it bubbles.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with fork; add Crisco thoroughly.
Mix until crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat water, egg and 1/2 cup vinegar.
Combine mixture.
Divide dough into 5 portions, shape into round patties for rolling, chill in plastic Ziploc bag 1/2 hour before rolling.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix liquid and eggs, then add beef, cracker crumbs and seasonings.
Form into 2 loaves.
Cover loaves with sauce.

title: steak roll-up supper
directions: Combine stuffing mix and water.
Spread each beef cubed steak with stuffing mixture.
Roll and fasten with wooden picks.
Brown beef rolls in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Drain.
Mix tomato sauce, salt, thyme, rosemary and poultry seasoning.
Add tomato sauce mixture and onions to skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 1 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except strawberries.
Cook until mixture is thick.
Set aside for at least 2 1/2 hours to cool at room temperature.
Place berries in pie shell and pour glaze over them.
Top with whipped cream.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles
until
tender
in salted water and drain. Melt butter in
skillet.
Add
meat
and cook, stirring, until meat has lost
red color. Drain. Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer
gently
for about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Combine
cottage
cheese,
sour
cream,
onion and noodles. Place half
of noodle mixture in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with meat mixture.	Repeat layers until all ingredients are used. Top
with
cheese.	Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: almond pine cone cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients but almonds; mix well.
Cover; chill overnight.
Form cheese mixture into shapes of 2 pine cones on serving platter.
Beginning at narrow end, press almonds at slight angle into cheese mixture in rows.
Continue overlapping rows until cheese is covered with appearance of pine cones.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour 1/2 of batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until toothpick tests clean.
Cool upright in pan for 25 minutes; then turn onto serving plate.

title: coconut pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs and coconut in milk.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, salt and butter.
Add to milk mixture.
Fold in beaten egg white.
Pour into greased baking dish. Set in a pan of hot water. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: southern living's chocolate date bars
directions: Combine dates, sugar, water and oleo in large saucepan.
Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until dates soften.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate until melted.
Beat in eggs.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with orange juice, then milk, blending well.
Stir in nuts and turn into well-greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or just until cake tests done.
Cool for 5 minutes, then spread with Orange Glaze. Let cake finish cooling after glazing.
While still warm, use a sharp knife to cut into 1 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Remove from pan when cool.
Freezes beautifully.
Yield:
56 bars.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 40 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together milk, water, vanilla and sugar.
Add broken pieces of bread.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
To bread mixture, add raisins, fruit cocktail, coconut and melted butter.
Beat eggs by hand and add to bread mixture.
Blend well by hand.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 hour.
Spoon into tall sherbet glasses to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 large servings.

title: chocolate mint dream cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Mix, then add 2 eggs.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut off the top of the cake through the center with a thread or very sharp knife, and add the following filling.
Save some for top of cake.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients over medium heat until boiling.
This sauce is good for salad dressing or can be used over ham, frankfurters, etc.
Keeps in refrigerator for a long period.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt margarine; add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Add pecans and enough milk to roll in balls.
Melt paraffin; add chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Dip candy balls in chocolate mixture. Place on wax paper to cool and dry.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Blend in sugar and melted butter.
Combine flour, cocoa, and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put scoop of ice cream over slice of pie.
Top with hot fudge sauce.

title: grandma frey's russian peppernuts
directions: Peel, core and chop apples.
Mix chopped apples with sugar. Make drop batter by sifting flour, salt and baking powder together, adding beaten egg and milk.
Stir in melted butter and mix apple pieces in batter until every piece is coated.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and press into 13 x 15-inch Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Chop almonds and toast at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Then sprinkle 1/2 cup on bottom of greased 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside remaining almonds and chocolate chips.
Measure remaining ingredients into mixer bowl.
Blend.
Then beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in chips and almonds.
Pour in pan.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix the flour, oleo (which has been melted) and pecans.
Press in bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix the instant pudding with milk.
Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip to cream cheese and spread half over bottom of crust.
Spread pudding over this.
Spread the remaining Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with a few nuts.
Put in refrigerator.

title: lemon or chocolate torte
directions: Soften the margarine.
Mix with flour and pecans.
Pat down in a 13 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: very devilish eggs(this is an original)
directions: Place eggs in cold water in medium saucepan.
Boil on high heat for 10 minutes.
Immediately pour off hot water and keep eggs in cold water, adding ice cubes.
This helps to peel easily.
Peel eggs.
Cut in half.
Scoop out hard-boiled yolks.
Beat egg yolks, hot and dry mustard, mayonnaise, salt and pepper until smooth. Electric blender works best.
When mixture is creamy, without lumps, mix in drained baby shrimp and spoon into egg white halves. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: dark zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs together.
Add
oil
and
brown
sugar.
Beat well. Add vanilla, zucchini
and	molasses.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add nuts. Bake
in greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Blend everything listed, sprinkle with salt and pepper, place in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until it bubbles throughout, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine and heat tomatoes, soups, taco sauce, chicken broth and cubed chicken. Line bottom of casserole dish with taco chips. Add chicken mixture. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly and hot.

title: hot punch or spiced tea
directions: Stir ingredients together to store; put in airtight container. Put 3 teaspoons in cup and add boiling water when serving.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and onion well in a Dutch oven; drain excess fat. Lower flame and add soups, taco sauce, green chilies, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Stir well.
Let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in rice well. Spread half of mixture in long oblong pan.
Top with crushed Doritos, then cheese.
Spread remaining mixture on top and cover with more cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar; let stand.
Put butter in 2-quart casserole.
Melt in 325° oven.

title: hot fudge pudding cake(read all recipe before starting cake.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour batter into square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In a small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter, then pour the hot water over top. (Do not stir.)

title: nana's hot ground beef dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in a skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly.
Drain and set aside.

title: secret ingredient meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle meat mixture with meat tenderizer before forming into loafs.
Put in a roaster and add 2 or 3 cans tomato soup over the top of loaves.
Bake at 275° until done.

title: lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook 15 minutes; drain and rinse.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 to 2 hours at 325°.
Stir occasionally.

title: million cheesecake-calories that is!!!!!
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add sugar, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes on center shelf of oven.
Turn off oven.
Open and let stand for 1 hour.
Cool completely.

title: cobbler
directions: Spray 9x15 pan with pam. Spread pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over filling. Pour 7-up over all and bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes. Serve warm are cold with fat free cool whip.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and toss.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown and drain chops.	Place in casserole.
Blend crumbs, onions, margarine, sage and 1/4 cup water.	Place over chops. Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: perfect muffins
directions: Grease 12 pan cups.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add egg, milk and shortening. Stir just to moisten dry ingredients.
Butter will be lumpy.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown (400°).

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil butter, cocoa and 1 cup water, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in sugar. Add flour and beat until smooth. Blend eggs and sour cream into mixture. Spread in greased oblong pan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. While warm, spread with Chocolate Frosting.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta just until tender. Drain. Add ice cubes to chill. Remove remaining cubes before adding veggies and dressing. Toss well and add dill weed.

title: pizza salad
directions: In large bowl or platter combine cheese, tomatoes, green peppers, pepperoni, onion and olives.
In small bowl combine tomato juice and salad dressing.
Pour over salad and toss.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle croutons over salad.

title: italian cream icing
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: sun maid raisins pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°. Grease 13 x 9 inch pan. Combine ingredients, except nuts and raisins, beat at low speed until moistened, then beat at medium 2 minutes. Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour into pan and bake 40 to 50 minutes. A good moist cake.

title: one dish chicken and rice bake(prep time: 5 minutes. cook time: 45 minutes.)
directions: Boil 2 chickens in salted water
until tender. Take off bone and cut into chunks.

title: fancy creamed chicken bake(a progressive dinner favorite)
directions: Wrap chicken with bacon.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish lined with the dried chipped beef.
Combine soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Bake for 3 hours at 300° uncovered.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in bottom of baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pork tenderloin may be used instead of pork chops.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Twenty-four hours ahead, mix all ingredients together.
Put in freezer overnight.
Next morning, stir with a wooden spoon every so often, putting back into freezer after each stirring.
To serve, fill glass 1/2 to 3/4 full with slush, then add 7-Up and serve.

title: state fair fried dough
directions: In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat. Meanwhile, separate the loaf of sough by pulling it apart into 1 - inch pieces.
Test the oil for readiness by carefully placing 1 piece of dough into the pan.
You'll know the oil is ready when the dough bubbles around the edged.
Place pieces of dough into the oil and fry a few at a until golden brown on the bottom.
Turn the dough over and brown the other side.
Remove from skillet with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Repeat until all the dough is fried.
Place the sugar in a shallow dish or a resealable plastic bag.
Roll or shake the fried dough in the sugar to coat completely.
Serve hot.
Yields 30 - 35 pieces.

title: potato dish
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas cake
directions: Sift together the sugar and flour; set aside.
Bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Add sugar and flour mixture; mix well.
Add eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake in sheet cake pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Ice warm.

title: chocolate eclair pudding
directions: Mix all 3 puddings with milk.
Combine Cool Whip and sour cream with pudding mix.

Layer bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan with graham crackers and pour 1/2 of the pudding mix on top, then add another layer of graham crackers and the remainder of the mix. Add another layer of graham crackers and top with the icing.

title: potato salad
directions: As potatoes and eggs cook, combine the first 4 ingredients and prepare remaining ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: squaw bread
directions: Mix thoroughly in order given.
Knead and roll out.
Cut out in squares.
Fry in hot oil.

title: carob fruit shake(serves 4)
directions: Place all ingredients into blender bowl.
Add 2 cups distilled water last.
Set blender on chop or mix setting and blend thoroughly.
You can add more fruit or distilled water until the desired consistency is reached.

title: anna radebaugh's caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, without stirring. Remove from heat and slowly pour over corn in two large, shallow roasting pans.
Mix well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pistachio instant pudding and pineapple with juice, mixing well. Mix in other ingredients. Chill well before serving. Enjoy!

title: rice salad
directions: Cover cooked rice and chill; add mayonnaise, celery, onion, mustard and salt to chilled rice; mix well.
Cover and chill. Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: three meat salad
directions: Grind or grate meatless corned beef, Chicken Style and Wham. Add chopped eggs, celery, green peppers and parsley.
Add mayonnaise.
Serve on beds of lettuce with crackers.

title: pork with browned rice
directions: Cook and stir celery, rice and onion in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until rice is golden brown and onion is tender. Stir in water, bouillon, soy sauce and pork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed (about 20 minutes).
Stir in green pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer.

title: basic 2 layer cake
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco, adding sugar slowly.
Mix well. Add eggs
one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Alternate flour, milk and vanilla.
Bake at 375° until done, about 20 minutes.

title: prairie potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 equal wedges; set aside. In a shallow dish, combine stuffing mix with spices.
Dip each potato wedge in melted butter, then coat with crumb mixture. Place wedges on greased baking sheet.
Pour remaining butter around wedges.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender. Serves 8.

title: strata sandwich
directions: Trim crust from bread; butter 1 side of each slice of bread. Put in a 5 x 5 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, butter side down.
Top with cheese and ham; place remaining bread slice on top, butter side up.
In bowl, beat together eggs, milk, mustard and a dash of salt and pepper.
Pour evenly over sandwich.
Cook on Medium-low or Power 3 (3%) for 9 minutes until egg mixture is set,
giving dish a quarter turn every 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 1 serving.
Total cooking time:
9 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs.
Add eggs and pour into a shallow Pyrex pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain. Set aside. Melt margarine and stir in flour. Gradually add milk and soup, stirring over low heat. Add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted. Continue stirring over low heat until soup thickens and bubbles. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tropical salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator in covered bowl overnight.

title: red cabbage
directions: Heat oil over medium-high heat; add cabbage, apples and water and cook until tender.
Add sugar to flour; moisten with vinegar to form a smooth paste.
Add to the cabbage and cook a few minutes until thickened slightly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: k c's rice o' mississippi
directions: Combine and cook in covered 1 1/2-quart dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir before serving as celery and onion tend to go to center.
This is especially good with poultry.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Tastes like pecan pie.

title: skillet date cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a pan; heat until the dates are melted, approximately 10 minutes. Cool mixture. Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts. Wet hands in cold water and roll cookie mixture into small balls. Roll in powdered sugar if desired. Makes 4 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a large pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake until cheese has melted.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Combine all ingredients, except wieners, in a large bowl suitable for the oven.
Add the wieners (split, if desired) to the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer, covered.
Serve on wiener buns with sauce as a topping.

title: okra salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Cook hominy and bell pepper until tender and most of hominy juice is gone.
Add Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup.
Bake 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: chicken dinner in the pot
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large, heavy ovenware pot (an enamel-coated cast-iron pot is best).
Peel potatoes; slice 1/2-inch thick and place on top of chicken.
Peel and quarter the onion.
Peel carrots; quarter lengthwise and cut into 2-inch lengths.
Cut ends off the green beans or separate frozen beans and place in the pot with onions and carrots.
Sprinkle contents of pot with parsley flakes.
Season lightly with pepper.
Pour sherry over all and cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, or until vegetables are tender.
Yield:
4 servings.
This is a low-fat recipe.

title: salmon steaks with dill sauce
directions: In glass baking dish arrange salmon.
Top with onion, bouillon, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, dill weed, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the water.
Cover with Handi-Wrap and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Melt butter and blend in flour and salt.
Blend in cream and mix until smooth.
Add juice from fish; stir in 2 tablespoons lemon juice and pour over fish.
Microwave 3 minutes until mixture boils or until done (time varies with thickness of steaks).
Garnish with sprigs of parsley.
Serves 4.

title: rich delmonico potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender.
Dice potatoes and place in greased medium-size casserole.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat and stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in cream and milk until mixture is smooth.
Return to medium-high heat and cook just to boiling, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and smooth.
Reduce heat to low and add 1 1/4 cups shredded Cheddar cheese, stirring until melted.
Pour sauce over potatoes in casserole.
Mix bread crumbs with remaining 1/4 cup cheese and spoon over casserole.
Dot surface with pats of butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until top is browned and sauce bubbling. Serves 6.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add extract, then beat the flour in slowly.
Fold in 7-Up.
Bake in a well greased floured tube pan or Bundt pan at 325° for an hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
You may add a glaze if desired.

title: green chili quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir in shredded Cheddar cheese, shredded Monterey Jack cheese and diced green chilies.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour until knife comes out clean.

title: cheese soup
directions: Blend butter, pepper and flour in large heavy soup pot. Add minced vegetables. Stir in milk gradually. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes. Stir frequently. Makes 2 quarts.

title: potato flake fish
directions: Mix eggs and milk together.
Put potato flakes in a separate bowl.
Dip fish into egg and milk mixture, then in potato flakes, salt and pepper.
Put fish in pan and fry until done.

title: ham stroganoff
directions: Cook rice as directed.
In separate pot, mix soup, milk, sour cream, thick slice of Velveeta cheese and ham.
When hot, mix with cooked rice.
For added taste, season with soy sauce.

title: high and mighty cream puffs
directions: Combine margarine and hot water in a heavy saucepan and put on range until margarine has melted and mixture has started to boil. Then add flour and salt, beating constantly.
Cook until mixture makes a ball.
This takes only a minute or two.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating hard after each addition.
Drop into ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 10 to 12 uniform mounds of dough.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When beads of moisture have disappeared, puffs are done.
Cool.
Cut off top.
Hollow out and fill with whipped cream or pudding.

title: favorite carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender-crisp.
Bring liquids and sugar to a boil. Mix in all other ingredients.
Marinate overnight before serving.
Drain.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: raspberry coconut bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs and butter. Spread evenly over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, pressing to make compact crust.
Sprinkle coconut over crust.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over coconut.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Spread jam over coconut layer; chill 3 to 4 hours.
Sprinkle with walnuts. Drizzle dark chocolate, then white chocolate over top layer to make lacy effect.
Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: lower fat alfredo sauce(1 cup)
directions: In medium-sized saucepan or double boiler, combine all the ingredients until everything is melted and the sauce is velvety smooth, about 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: braunschweiger kabobs
directions: On skewer, alternate 2 cubes sausage and 1 each: pineapple chunk, cherry and cheese cube.
Yields 12 kabobs.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat together with rotary beater. Pour into 9-inch pie pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 425°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or more.

title: peanut candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until spins a thread.
Add butter, then peanuts.
Cook until peanuts begin to pop.
Add soda and stir quickly.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan which has been lined with foil, if desired.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.
Take out; drain off fat and put in oven for a minute or two longer.
Serves 6.

title: pot roast
directions: Put roast in crock-pot. Add water and soup mix. Cover and cook until meat is tender. Make gravy from stock by thickening with cornstarch.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
When cool, peel and mash to make 1 1/2 cups.
To the sweet potatoes, add butter, sugar, eggs and remainder of ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Then lower oven temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix butter and cheese. Slowly mix in flour to a crumbly state, then with hands, mix together.
Use cookie press to make cheese straws.

title: one-dish turkey dinner
directions: Prepare stuffing mix using package directions.
Spoon stuffing onto turkey slices; roll up to enclose filling.
Place in greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture of soup and evaporated milk over rolls.
Cook broccoli for half the time suggested in package directions; drain.
Arrange over rolls.
Sprinkle with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook broccoli and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
In bowl thoroughly mix cream of chicken soup, milk, water and cheese.
Stir in uncooked rice and the drained broccoli-onion mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole. Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, stirring once.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: hot chicken wings over rice
directions: Stir-fry chicken 3-5 minutes.

title: broccoli mousse
directions: Mix the gelatin in cold water; add then to hot consomme soup. Dissolve gelatin in hot soup and set aside.

title: mixed vegetable meat loaf
directions: Place vegetables, onion, garlic, bell pepper, bread crumbs and egg into food processor or blender.
Process until ingredients are pasty.
Add mixture to ground round.
Mix thoroughly; add salt and Tony Chachere's.
Form into loaf.
Place into pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus for 8 minutes.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place asparagus in shallow bowl and pour marinade over it.
Chill at least 8 hours before serving.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad dressing in large bowl.
Dissolve soda in water.
Stir salt into flour and add to sugar mixture, a little at a time, alternating with water mixture.
Mix well.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until cake tests done.

title: dainty lily cookies
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter.
Then add flour.
Roll out and cut with 2 1/2-inch round cutter.
Roll into cornucopia by bringing two (2) rounded edges together and letting them overlap. Press them gently and shape like a lily.
Fill open part with a little jelly or orange marmalade.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Drench with 10x sugar.
Depending on the size, makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: rice and beans creole style
directions: Notice:
If making rice that takes at least 30 minutes, start it before the beans.
Make sure all ingredients are chopped and all cans are opened before beginning.

title: southern creamed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until warm.

title: ham salad sandwiches
directions: Salad dressing to mix well so it's not dry.
Chill.
Make sandwiches.
Can freeze leftover for a week.
Makes good finger sandwiches for parties.

title: yogurt cream frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and yogurt.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill before using.

title: barley, corn and avocado salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together vinegar and olive, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp, about 8 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, transfer the bacon to paper towels to drain.
Discard fat from the saucepan, add barley, salt and 2 cups of water to pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and maintain a simmer until barley is tender. Drain and press out excess moisture.
Transfer to a serving bowl. Add corn, red onions, bacon, and dressing.
Toss thoroughly.
Add tomatoes and avocados and toss gently.
(Let salad stand at room temperature before serving if it has been refrigerated.)

title: paradise salad
directions: Mix Jello and water then add remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and pat in bottom of a rectangular Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool, then mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Place the mixture over cooled crust.
Top with blueberry pie filling (one can).

title: cream cheese and rum pie
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Prepare crust by melting the butter, then adding the crushed graham crackers.
Mix well.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with this mixture and bake for 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool, but leave oven on.

title: bread sticks
directions: Melt margarine in rectangle baking dish. Combine flour and milk. Stir until dough leaves sides of bowl. Knead several times on floured board. Roll into 3 inch wide rectangle.
Cut in half lengthwise. Cut crosswise into strips. Place over melted margarine in baking dish. Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: play dough for children
directions: Cook until thick.
Turn out on flat surface.
Mix in colors and knead until smooth.
Cut with cookie cutters.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Use reserved fruit juice and enough water to make 2 cups of liquid. Heat until boiling. Add gelatin; dissolve and let stand for a few minutes. Add the tray of ice cubes and stir until gelatin mixture is cold. Remove the unmelted ice cubes and add drained blueberries and pineapple.

Refrigerate until congealed. Cream together the sugar, cream cheese and vanilla. Fold in 1/2 pint of sour cream and spread over congealed salad. Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: eggnog cake
directions: Grease generously a Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan with soft butter or margarine.
Press whole almonds and candied cherries against buttered sides and bottom making a pretty pattern.
Dust lightly with flour.
Set aside.

In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, nutmeg, eggs, eggnog, melted butter and rum or rum flavoring. Beat until smooth, about 4 minutes, with an electric mixer on medium speed or about 450 strokes by hand.
Pour batter into decorated pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 45 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when pressed lightly.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes; invert on rack and cool thoroughly.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: crusty cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add cream cheese and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and eggs alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 75 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan to wire rack.
Serve with Berried Treasure.

title: ho-made ice cream
directions: Combine to just a heat the milk, sugar and eggs.
Add Pet milk, Eagle Brand and 2 teaspoons of vanilla.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
Place in ice cream freezer and turn!

title: old time favorite
directions: Bake in a 1 1/2-quart dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute the leeks and onion in the butter until they are soft and golden, but not brown.
Slice the potatoes thinly and arrange a third of the slices in a buttered baking dish.
Spread half of the sauteed vegetables over them.
Put in another third of the potatoes, then the rest of the vegetables and bay leaf and finish with the rest of the potatoes.
(Sprinkle a little pepper between layers, but no salt).
Fill the dish just to the level of the top layer of potatoes with
chicken stock or consomme; dot generously with butter and bake in a very slow oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, or until the potatoes are done, the liquid is absorbed and the top is delicately browned.
Serves 4.

title: french pear pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg slightly.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Mix together sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.
Add to sour cream mixture and mix well.
Quarter pears and arrange in shallow baking dish.
Top with the sour cream mixture.
Bake 15 minutes. While pudding bakes, combine brown sugar, 1/3 cup flour and nutmeg in another small bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Sprinkle over pudding and then bake another 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: danish cucumber salad
directions: With sharp knife, cut cucumbers into paper-thin slices. In large bowl, mix slices with 2 teaspoons salt. Let stand at room temperature 1 hour. Drain liquid from cucumbers. Stir in vinegar, sugar, chopped dill, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt until thoroughly mixed. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate salad at least 3 hours before serving.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, egg and butter.
Pat onto cookie sheet and top with chocolate chips.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese; mix well and pour over top.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix as directed on box.
Add oranges and beat thoroughly. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all together, except chopped pecans.
Form into balls.
Cut in half.
Makes two balls.
Roll in pecans.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients, roll into a log and roll in crushed pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup at
a time, into egg yolks.
Mix good. May require more flour.
Knead.
Roll out thin.
Let dry.
Cut in noodle size strips
or use a noodle cutter.
Let thoroughly dry. Store in bags or airtight container.

title: swedish baked rice
directions: Cook rice, water and salt until done.
Blanch and drain.
Cook rice mixture and milk for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add well beaten eggs, slowly, and continue cooking for a few minutes.
Add cornstarch, sugar and almond extract.
Place in a large casserole. Cover with meringue of about 3 egg whites plus 6 tablespoons sugar. Place in a 350° oven, until browned.
Serve warm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, then add 1 stick (1/2 cup) melted butter to mixture.
Pour into large baking dish and cover with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: summer fruit with brown-sugar cream
directions: Mix sour cream and brown sugar in a bowl.
Divide melon and berries among dessert dishes.
Top with sour cream mixture and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: mexe-bean salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and let marinate in refrigerator all day or overnight.
Just before serving, add lettuce and corn chips; toss well.
This salad is always a hit at barbecues!

title: knox blox
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set and cut into squares.
Eat with your fingers.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Wash and drain fish. Combine yogurt, oil, lemon juice and seasoning in a shallow dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on wax paper. Dip fish in yogurt mixture and then press in crumbs. Coat both sides. Place fish on slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 475 in oven for 10 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Dissolve cubes in boiling water.
Blend all ingredients in blender.
Serve with carrot sticks, celery sticks, bell pepper strips, cauliflower and cucumbers.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Refrigerate 8 hours.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: stack cake
directions: Melt 1 cup shortening in saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup molasses, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup buttermilk.
Warm over medium heat, then remove to cool.
Add 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in a chopper and mix to desired consistency.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: kalua casserole
directions: Layer bread, cheese and seafood in buttered casserole dish. Pour melted butter over layers.
Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt; pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: heavenly cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2 prepared graham cracker pie crusts.
Chill at least 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bisquick quiche
directions: Put all ingredients, except ham and cheese, in blender and mix together.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Add cheese and ham on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in order of appearance in the recipe.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.
Allow to cool for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve!

title: best cheese cake
directions: Thoroughly blend the first 2 ingredients and 1/4 cup sugar. Press firmly in bottom of pie pan and 2 1/2-inches up sides.
Bake until fluffy.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until firm.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease pans with shortening. Flour the sides and bottom lightly. Mix 1/2 cup warm water with cream cheese. Add cake mix, 1/2 cup sugar, oil, eggs and 3 tablespoons butter. Beat at medium speed for 3 to 4 minutes. Pour into cake pans. Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on wire rack.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat together eggs, 1 cup butter and powdered sugar for 15 minutes,
no
less.
Mix graham crackers and melted butter. Spread in a
x	13-inch
pan.
Pour egg mixture over crust. Slice bananas;
sprinkle	with
lemon juice to maintain color. Put banana
slices on top of egg mixture.
Put drained pineapple over bananas.
Cover
with
whipped
cream.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: snack recipe for sweet 'n nutty snack mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Put butter in a large, shallow roasting pan and place in oven until melted.
Remove from oven and stir in sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add popcorn and noodles and stir until coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in almonds and raisins.
When cool, store in airtight container.
Yields 11 cups.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour over flank steak in a shallow pan. Turn meat once or twice.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Barbecue or broil meat, then slice meat thin to serve.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover head of cabbage with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Peel off 12 nice leaves.
Combine beef, salt, pepper, rice, onion, egg and poultry seasoning.
Place equal portions in center of each leaf.
Fold sides of leaf over meat and roll up. Place in small casserole.
Combine water, lemon juice and tomato sauce and pour over rolls.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate bourbon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a small saucepan combine sugar, corn syrup, and butter. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until butter melts and sugar dissolves. Cool slightly. In a large bowl combine eggs, bourbon, vanilla and salt. Mix well. Slowly pour sugar mixture into egg mixture, whisking constantly. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Pour mixture into pie shell. Bake in preheated oven for 50 - 55 minutes, or until set and golden. May be served warm or chilled.

title: wilbur's homemade ice cream
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly and with beater running, add 2 tablespoons white Karo syrup.
Continue beating and add the condensed milk, evaporated milk, sugar and vanilla flavoring and wash out both cans with homogenized milk.
Have on hand 1 quart milk.
Fold milk mixture into beaten egg whites.
Pour into freezer can.
Add fruit as desired and enough milk to fill freezer 3/4 plus full. Freeze.
Remove dasher and allow to ripen.

title: cheddar egg bake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into ungreased square baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first six ingredients. Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in a bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter.
Mix only until flour is moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: southern style dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 300° oven until top is golden brown.
Don't overbake or it will be tough.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain off grease. Add both cans of tomato sauce and an equal amount of water.
Pour juice from the whole tomatoes into soup pan.
Chop tomatoes; add to soup pan.
Add kidney beans and bring to boil.
Add cabbage and cook until cabbage is tender, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until firm.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips over low heat.
Cool slightly. Add nut meats and marshmallows.
Spread coconut on wax paper. Pour mixture onto coconut and roll into long roll.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Cut into slices.

title: chocolate pie(makes two 8-inch pies)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks and blend in milk and water.
Combine sugar, flour and cocoa; add to yolk mixture. Transfer to a large saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture has thickened, cool slightly and pour into chilled pie shells.
Makes 2 large or 6 small pies.

title: tomato and broccoli bake
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salt water 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese and flour, set aside.
In a large saucepan cook onion and garlic in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes, parsley, oregano, basil and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Bring to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Simmer, covered. Transfer to an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Blend in flour and spices.
Alternately with juice.
Mix until smooth.
Coat fruit and nuts in 1/2 c. extra flour and add to other mixture.
Grease tube pan.
Line bottom with wax paper.
Bake 300° about 2 hours.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Using a small knife, rub crushed garlic thoroughly
into both sides of each pork chop.
Lightly sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.

title: sour cream apple cake
directions: In mixing bow, mix apples, 1/2 tsp. cinnamon, 1/2 tsp. nutmeg and 1 Tbsp. sugar.
In skillet, melt 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 c. sugar on medium to high heat; stir until syrupy.
Spread apples evenly over bottom of pan.
Remove from heat.
With electric mixer, cream together 1 1/2 c. sugar and 1 stick butter.
Add 1 tsp. cinnamon, 1/2 tsp. nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour.
Beat well.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes.

title: dill pickles (refrigerator)
directions: Using a wide-mouthed gallon jar, layer:
layer of cucumbers, grape leaf, dill branch and garlic clove.
Repeat until jar is full.
Make a liquid of water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil and cool slightly.
Pour over pickles and refrigerate at least 2 days.
Can be kept all year.
Triple the juice recipe to make 2 gallons of pickles.

title: special white cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add extract to flour mixture along with milk and blend well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into three greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix the strawberries, rhubarb, sugar, rind and flour together in a bowl.
Set aside.

title: heath sensation cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour milk over the cake.
Spread caramel topping over the cake.
Top cake with Cool Whip and Heath candy bar pieces.

title: rice krispy bars
directions: Heat syrup, sugar and peanut butter until sugar is well dissolved.
Add Rice Krispies.
Lightly pat in a greased 11 x 14 pan.
DO NOT PRESS!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple (undrained) with the dry pudding mix.
Stir well. Add whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir by hand.
Pour into dish or mold; chill.
May be served on lettuce as a salad or dessert.
Also can be frozen.
Serves 6 to 9 persons.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling, slightly salted water. Drain. Saute carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons margarine. Stir in 1 1/2 cups croutons, soup, sour cream and cheese. Gently add zucchini to mixture. Place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Melt remaining butter. Add rest of croutons.
Toss and sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pork pork chu chu yum yum
directions: In a shallow baking pan, combine 1 tablespoon of soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add the pork and marinate for 30 minutes.

title: mindy's pot roast
directions: Thaw roast. Place in roasting dish. Peel potatoes, halve and place around roast. Place carrots around roast. Add a few onion slices.

title: grandma's meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ingredients and form a loaf.
Place in shallow pan in moderate oven (350°).

title: nancy ware cake
directions: Into cake mix, add oranges with juice, eggs and vegetable oil, beat about 3 minutes until the batter is fluffy.

title: southern maryland stuffed ham
directions: Remove
skin from ham.
With fat side up, pierce with a long thin knife, a row of slits about 1 inch apart and as deep as possible
without
going
through
bottom.
On
second row stagger the
slits
from
the first row and continue piercing rows as far back as possible.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well until smooth.
Put batter in 3 bread pans (greased and floured).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done in center.
Cool on rack. Keep bread 1 day before serving, refrigerated or may be frozen.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello.
Add lemon juice and salt; set aside.
Dilute cream cheese, milk and other ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop green tomatoes, cabbage, cucumbers, green bell peppers, onions and hot peppers.
(May be very fine if you like.)
Mix together with salt and cover with ice.
Let stand for 2 hours. Drain.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, beat thoroughly.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add peanuts, if desired.
Drop onto greased pan.
Press lightly with potato masher.
Bake at 300° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yield:
280 cookies.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Let cheese and butter sit at room temperature until soft. Blend together with mixer.
Add other ingredients, one at a time, mixing each thoroughly.
Eventually you may have to mix by hand as it gets too stiff for the beater.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups of the sifted flour into large bowl of mixer.
Add yeast and blend at #3 speed 1/2 minute.
Combine milk, 1/2 cup water, oil, sugar and salt in a small saucepan.
Heat on low heat until mixture is just warm.
Add to dry ingredients in the mixer bowl and beat at #3 speed until smooth.
Add eggs and beat at #4 speed until mixture is blended.
Turn to #1 speed and gradually add 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth and well-blended. Scrape beaters.

title: gulumpkies(or polish stuffed cabbage)
directions: Saute onions in butter.
In large kettle, fill with water to boil for cabbage.
Beat egg and add in enough milk to make 1/2 cup. Put cabbage in boiling water and separate the leaves.
Place meat mixture in large bowl; add egg and milk mixture, rice and all the seasonings.
Mix well with hands.
Add sauteed onions and blend well.
Cut thick core off cabbage leaves.
Lay aside.
Add the meat mixture in each cabbage leave, one at a time.
Roll the leaf up. Place Gulumpkies in oblong baking pan.
Pour tomato juice over the stuffed cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with sour cream and chives on top.

title: pickled red beets
directions: Scrub beets and boil until tender; peel and drop into brine.

title: chocolate-caramel popcorn
directions: Remove unpopped kernels from popped corn.
In a 17 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan, combine the popcorn, peanuts and sunflower nuts, if desired; set aside.

title: old timey buttermilk pie
directions: Cut butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time; add flour.
Stir in milk and extract.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for
40 to 50 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: fried green beans
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Pour beans into nonstick fry skillet.
Crumble bacon over beans and oil.
Cook, uncovered, until all moisture is gone and beans are lightly brown. Serve hot.

title: picante chicken 'n rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in oil in 10-inch skillet for 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Arrange chicken breasts over rice.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand covered until all liquid is absorbed. Garnish with avocado, tomato and cheese.
Serves 6.

title: bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat water to lukewarm and add yeast, sugar and salt.
Begin adding flour and mixing until dough gets heavy.
Turn dough over onto a floured work area and knead dough until it is very stiff.
Roll dough into a ball and place it in an oiled bowl.
Cover and place in an undrafty spot to rise.
When it has risen, punch down.
Sprinkle with flour and knead again.
Place dough in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake until golden brown.
When removed from oven, butter top and remove from pan.
Butter sides and bottom, also.

title: fudgy chocolate layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. In a saucepan, melt butter and chocolate, stirring, over low heat. Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large bowl of electric mixer. Add chocolate mixture, buttermilk and eggs. Beat on low speed for 1 minute. Increase speed to high and beat until soft and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Divide batter between cake pans. Bake until cakes spring back when gently pressed, 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans 5 minutes. Invert onto wire rack.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy and smooth.
Very good on carrot cake or spice cake.

title: mixed veggie bake
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli in small pieces; cook.
Drain 1 can of mushrooms; reserve liquid from 2nd can.
Layer veggies and 1/2 can of French fried onions in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: i want to live again twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Wash potatoes well.
Cut two small slits in each potato, then cook all at once in microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Bake potatoes in preheated oven for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out insides, leaving a thin shell.
In a mixing bowl, combine potato insides, cream cheese, butter, salt and pepper, milk and chives.
Mash until smooth.
Spoon mixture into potato shells.
Return potatoes to oven and bake, uncovered, until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cheddar cheese.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine ingredients into a 13 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: extra fancy main dish
directions: Shred cabbage. Drain mushrooms.
Cook and drain noodles.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and mix with remaining ingredients. Save a few oranges and garnish the top. Salad is ready to serve.

title: cheese-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut each tomato in half; scoop out tomato pulp, reserving for other uses.
Combine cottage cheese and next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into each tomato.
Sprinkle with green onions.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: *Can use 2 cubes of chicken base or 2 tsp. instant broth instead of soup.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in tube pan.
Grease pan well.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.
Put cake in before turning oven on.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Thoroughly mix eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini together.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add flavoring, raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler. Add sugar. Beat the eggs and add to mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased pie pan and cook at 300° for 25 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: buttery breadsticks
directions: Pour melted margarine onto an 11 x 17-inch baking sheet. Roll each roll to about 6-inches in margarine until completely coated.
Place cheese in separate bowl and roll buttered breadsticks in cheese.
Place breadsticks on baking sheet in 2 vertical rows of twelve each.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, if desired.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise until double in size. Remove wrap and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 24 breadsticks.

title: mother's chocolate pie
directions: Boil all together until thick.
Add one teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Boil sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let set.

title: cannelloni with prosciutto and zucchini
directions: Bring the water to a boil in a large pot; cook the cannelloni shells for half the time directed on the package.
Drain the shells and place them on a baking sheet to cool.
Preheat oven to 400°; heat the olive oil in large saut pan on high heat until sizzling, about 2 minutes.
Add the zucchini, garlic, red pepper flakes, onion, salt and pepper and cook about 8 to 10 minutes. Add the wine and chicken stock and boil until most of the liquid cooks away (about 4 to 5 minutes).

Place the zucchini mixture in a food processor with the Ricotta, 1/3 cup of Parmesan cheese, the Prosciutto (or ham) and parsley; process to a smooth consistency. Transfer the filling to a piping bag with a large open tip.
Place the tip in one end of the cannelloni and fill halfway; place the tip in the other end of the shell and finish filling.
(If you don't have a piping bag, cut each cannelloni shell open lengthwise, lay on a flat surface and spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons of the filling down the center and roll up.)

title: mozzarella stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms.
Toss mushrooms in melted butter in broiler pan and arrange cut ends up.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs and spoon mixture onto each mushroom top.
Adorn with an olive slice.
Broil for approximately 8 minutes until cheese is melted and mushrooms are tender.

title: turkey noodle parmesan
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, prepare noodles according to package directions; drain.
In same saucepan, combine soup, milk, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and black pepper.
Add noodles and turkey.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with parsley and Parmesan cheese when serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and add baking powder, soda and salt. Add nuts and mix.
Melt shortening in saucepan.
Remove from heat. Mix in sugar.
(Add 1 tablespoon hot water if vegetable shortening is used.)
Cool,
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, small amount at a time, mixing well.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut in 24 bars.

title: cashew tuna casserole
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup chow mein noodles.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine the rest of the noodles and remaining ingredients. Sprinkle reserved noodles on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients, except broccoli. Place frozen broccoli in the middle.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour.

title: spicy corn-on-the-cob
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix butter, crushed pepper, cumin and salt in small bowl until blended.
Place each ear on 12-inch square foil.
Spread each ear evenly with about 1 tablespoon butter mixture.
Bring up foil so edges meet on top and fold both edges together twice to seal, leaving some air space around corn.
Twist ends of foil to seal.
Bake 15 minutes or until corn is tender. Open foil carefully to avoid being burned by steam.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade noodle dough
directions: Sift flour with salt into a mixing bowl.
Make a "well" in the center.
Drop in eggs.
Combine with a fork, adding spoonfuls of water as necessary to form a ball of dough.
Knead for 5 minutes. Roll out on a lightly floured board.
When the dough is rolled evenly, let set 20 minutes to dry.
Roll up lightly and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Let dry thoroughly 2 hours.

title: chinese ribs
directions: Select small bone pork ribs and slice to 1 bone (3 to 4 pounds or
1 slab).
Place in deep pan after rinsing off meat. Mix together
all
ingredients
and
pour over ribs.
Let set overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Cook in oven at 400° for 1 hour.

title: steak or chicken marinade
directions: Marinate 2 to 3 hours, turning occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken with remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake casserole in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs and paprika.

title: fat-free bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, milk and sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add egg and applesauce.
Mix in dry ingredients until moist.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes in lined muffin tins.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water (salted). Drain. Add soup, sour cream and water chestnuts. Separately
mix melted butter and herb dressing. Put half of dressing mix in bottom of baking dish. Add squash mixture. Cover with remaining dressing mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay each package of rolls on a cookie sheet.
Pinch together the perforations and bake as directed.
Let cool.

title: strawberries and cream dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in cup of hot water.
Stir in frozen strawberries and stir in vanilla ice cream.
Pour in loaf cake pan; put in freezer.
Ready to serve in approximately 1 hour.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries, nuts, bananas and pineapple.
Put 1/2 of mixture (approximately 3 cups) in a large bowl and chill 2 1/2 hours.
Leave other 1/2 at room temperature.
Spread sour cream over the chilled mixture and the remaining mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, milk and cream cheese in a large bowl. Beat on low speed.
Add powdered sugar and Cool Whip, mixing until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Before serving, drizzle chocolate syrup over top of pie.
Store leftovers in freezer.
Serves 6.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in bottom of casserole.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Mix together soup, salad dressing and lemon juice. Pour over chicken. Add cheese.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Place buttered crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: basic pancake recipe
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, vegetable oil and milk until consistency desired.
Add sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Add optionals as desired.
Cook and enjoy.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Be sure sugar is dissolved.
Marinate chicken or other meat as desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In
large bowl, mix together all casserole ingredients. Pour into a
13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Great for dinner party.
Can be made early and heated before serving.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer half of lettuce, the eggs and onion.
Then put second layer of lettuce, bacon and peas.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise and spread on top to the very edge of the bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or at least overnight.
When ready to serve, spread cheese on top of dressing and toss to mix salad ingredients.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken and salt (to taste) in large pot.
Cover with water.
Let cook until tender.
Remove chicken from pot.
Let cool; remove the bones.
Put chicken back in broth; set aside. Mix the flour, shortening, salt and baking powder together.
Add 2/3 cup milk.
Mix together.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Grease hot griddle with butter; pour about 1/3 cup batter per pancake onto the griddle.
Flip when tiny bubbles appear.
Pancakes are thinner than most and very moist. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and raisins; add syrup, if desired.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Save 1 1/2 quarts of broth.
Do not drain.
Add onions, peppers and diced cheese (remaining ingredients).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be frozen.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix everything except egg whites.
Then beat egg whites until stiff and add 1/4 cup white sugar.
Then mix egg whites last into pie mix.
Makes 4 pies.
Bake at 325°.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter in 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.
Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoon milk until smooth, fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip, spread over crust and arrange strawberries.
Using 3 1/2 cups milk prepare pudding as directed on package, pour over berries.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Shortly before serving spread remaining Cool Whip and garnish with berries.

title: holiday date balls
directions: Cook margarine, sugar, dates and egg together (stove top or microwave) about 2 to 5 minutes (until smooth and hot).
Remove from fire and add Rice Krispies and nuts.
When mixture is cool enough to handle, grease hands and roll mixture into balls.
Coat with confectioners sugar. Mmm!!!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add enough water to syrup from pineapple to make 1 cup and add to Jell-O.
Stir in cranberry sauce; add drained pineapple.
Pour in flat Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar good.
Add oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed butter and sugars.
Mix good.
Roll into little balls and press on cookie sheet.
Press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Miracle Whip, eggs, water and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add carrots and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with desired frosting.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs. Add milk, saltines, onions, salt and pepper. Add beef and mix well. Shape into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients. Spread 3/4 cup over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 or or until no pink remains. Drain. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing. Serve with remaining sauce. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and layer as follows:
first, chips; second, chicken; third, mix together broth, soups and Ro-Tel and pour over chicken and chips; fourth, top with cheese slices.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cake:
Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs, cocoa and flour, beating after each addition.
Thoroughly beat mixture; fold in coconut and nuts and mix well.
Add up to 1/2 cup of milk if needed to thin mixture.
Prepare sheet cake pan or three 9-inch pans with Baker's Joy; pour in mixture and bake at 350° until cake will pass the "toothpick test" for doneness.

title: crab pate
directions: In a bowl mix all ingredients except mushroom soup and gelatin.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly.
In a saucepan heat mushroom soup until very warm.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 or 3 tablespoons of hot water.
Mix dissolved gelatin with soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Add soup mixture to remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into greased mold.
Chill until set.
Remove to a serving tray.

title: vegetables in cream sauce
directions: *Such as carrots, peas, green beans, spinach.

title: golden fried eggplant
directions: Cut the eggplant into slices 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Let drain on paper towels for 30 minutes; pat dry.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pepperoni cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients reserving 1/4 cup pecans.
Shape into ball.
Cover with remaining pecans.

title: banana split pie(serves 8)
directions: Slice banana and layer on bottom of chocolate pie crust. Sprinkle pineapple over banana.
Mix pudding and milk according to package directions.
Pour over pineapple and banana.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Slice strawberries on top of pudding.
Top with whipped topping.
Drizzle chocolate sauce over top.
Cut cherries in half and garnish top with cherries.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust: Flatten crescent rolls in jelly roll pan or pizza pan. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes; cool.

title: chicken dish
directions: Mix pineapple and apricot preserves, Russian dressing and onion soup all together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan; put chicken parts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: sweet milk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add liquid.

title: quick and easy chicken noodles
directions: Cook egg noodles until tender in salted water.
Drain and rinse.
Add margarine, salt, pepper, parsley and soup to noodles. Heat in microwave for 2 minutes, then stir.
Goes great with English peas, a salad and rolls.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocado and remove seed.
Mash avocado up.
Add lemon juice, mayonnaise and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 teaspoon cajun seasoning.
Add tomato.
Serve with tortilla chips or tacos.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Using self-rising flour, make a hole in center of flour and pour in mixture.
Work in flour until dough is firm enough to roll out on floured cloth.
(Roll fairly thin.)
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° until brown.
(Will cook fast.)
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: oleta easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by package directions, using 2 layers.
Allow to cool and cut in half to make 4 layers.
(A nylon thread is good to split the layers.)

title: chicken "chicharrones"
directions: Chicken should be kept in refrigerator at least one day after cleaning and cutting into small pieces.
