Mix lemon juice, soya sauce and 3/4 teaspoon salt; pour over chicken and leave in this seasoning at least 1/2 hour.
Mix flour, pepper, paprika and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a paper bag.
Put pieces of chicken into bag and shake well to flour (2 or 3 pieces at a time).
Fry in oil until golden brown.
It depends on the size of the pan used for frying on how many pieces can be fried together.
Never fry too many together to avoid cooling of the oil.
Serve with lemon slices.

title: pork roast "drunk pig"
directions: Prepare roast for oven by making wells in roast (stick knife into roast, then stick your finger in the hole).
Place a piece of garlic (not whole pod, maybe half or third if big pods) in bottom of hole, then fill the hole with salt.
Place roast in roasting pan.
Rub salt all over roast, then pepper and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Brown roast at 450° for approximately 30 minutes. Pour wine over roast after browned to leave about 1/4-inch in bottom of pan.
Baste every 15 minutes with wine.
Decrease temperature to 350° after 45 minutes.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 1/2 hours according to size of roast.
If wine begins to dry in bottom of pan, add more.

title: cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Mix the cheese and jello mixture together. Add vanilla.
Beat Carnation milk until stiff.
Add cheese and jello mixture and beat 2 minutes.
Add pineapple.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together, then pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: front porch lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and boiling water in bowl, stirring until sugar dissolves. Add lemon juice and cold water; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Pour over ice filled glasses.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: belgium or summer salad
directions: Drain first 3 vegetables, then add last 4 ingredients.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft.
While potatoes bake, fry and crumble bacon.
When potatoes finish baking, scoop out pulp and save both pulp and shell.
Mix pulp with sour cream, chives, butter, eggs, salt and pepper.
Blend in bacon.
Refill potato shells and wrap in foil and freeze.
When you are ready to use them, bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook until thickens.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and mixture.
Beat again until blended.
Spread on pie filling and brown in 400° oven.
Makes enough for 1 large pie or 2 small pies.

title: date nut sauce pudding
directions: Bring to boil; stir well.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake 1 hour in 350°
oven.
Top with whipping cream.

title: a great tomato soup
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Add all other ingredients, except butter and flour.
Boil 30 minutes.
Put through strainer.
Melt butter. Blend in flour slowly.
Add a little of the soup.
When smooth combine and simmer 3 minutes and seal in Mason jars.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Stir sugar and syrup over low heat.
Bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Remove from heat and fold in cornflakes.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: kentucky fried chicken(original recipe)
directions: Shake and coat chicken with combined ingredients, then put margarine on top.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen bread dough caramel rolls(otherwise known as "sticky buns")
directions: Let bread dough thaw completely.
(Thawing in the microwave is not recommended).
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear 1 loaf into pieces and put in pan.
Melt margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour mixture over bread dough in pan.
Tear second loaf into pieces and put in pan.
Let rise until doubled (about 2 hours).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bread in center is done.

title: far east eggplant
directions: Cook ingredients except cheese and bacon in a large skillet until tender (I cover it).
Top with cheese and bacon in a 2-quart casserole and brown under broiler.

title: sausage dip
directions: Fry sausage until crumbled in little pieces. Drain. Melt cream cheese and tomatoes and chiles together in a frying pan. Then add cooked sausage and stir together well. When ready to serve, put in crock-pot to keep warm or warm in microwave. May add a little water when reheating, if needed. Serve with Tostitos chips or Ritz crackers.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and peanut butter, add cereal, stir gently.
Put in a large zip lock bag and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Shake gently.
Lay out on wax paper to dry.

title: cream soup from scratch
directions: This is a dry mix that can be stored in an airtight container and kept on hand until needed.

title: pork chops polynesian
directions: Lightly salt pork chops.
Brown chops in oil in large skillet, about 5 minutes per side.
Combine tomato paste, crushed pineapple and juice, soy sauce, brown sugar and ginger.
Top browned chops with about 2/3 cup sauce.
Add water to skillet.
Cover; reduce heat and continue cooking 20 minutes or until pork chops are tender.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with chops.

title: mississippi corn salad
directions: Slice green onions and their tops.
Stir all together in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 to 24 hours.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Stir all ingredients except candy bar over low heat until all are blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Let cool.
Melt the candy bar and pour over mixture.
When chocolate is firm, cut in squares.
Don't refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat together the sweet potatoes (making 1 1/2 cups mashed sweet potatoes) and mix together with rest of the ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in bowl.
Add beaten eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate over night for best taste.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In a crock or chefs pot, saute mushrooms and pepper slices in olive oil until tender.
Then add other ingredients and cook at 225-250°, stirring occasionally, for 3 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Thoroughly combine beaten eggs and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla, rice and raisins in a vegetable spray coated 1 1/2-quart dish. Mix; place dish in a pan filled 1-inch deep with very hot water. Place in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
After 30 minutes in oven, stir carefully for good distribution.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Mix pineapple (crushed) with juice with the Eagle Brand milk. Stir in pie filling and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pretty bowl and chill.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in extra large bowl.
Pour butter popcorn oil over dry mixture and mix thoroughly.
Best if allowed to sit a day or two to exchange flavors, but not necessary.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix and chill dough.
Roll in balls and make a thumbprint in center.
Fill with preserves.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets 10 minutes and cool on racks.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
These cookies are not so sweet, but with they jelly they are flavorful.

title: betty's coleslaw
directions: Wash and dry all vegetables.
In a large bowl, grate vegetables.
Mix in mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and black pepper; mix well.
Taste and adjust seasonings, if needed.
Best if made the day before using.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Chill for at least 1 hour and serve.

title: settler's beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon separately.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Simmer.
The longer it simmers the better.
Serve with cornbread.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream together 1 cup margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and oats. Mix well.
In a heavy saucepan, put milk, chocolate chips, 2 tablespoons margarine and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir until smooth. Remove from heat and stir in nuts and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Put 2/3 of oat mixture in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over oat layer.
Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
I melt milk chip mixture in a slow cooker.
Yields 25 bars.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Arrange in bottom of greased baking dish. Layer chicken over top of broccoli. Combine next 3 ingredients together and pour over broccoli and chicken. Combine bread crumbs and butter over top. Bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: wanda's chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar until dissolved.
Add corn syrup and melted butter; mix well.
Add pecans.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on bottom of pie crust.
Pour pecan mixture over chips.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, or until done.
Cool before serving.

title: dinosaur food
directions: Mix dirt and swamp water.
Add crushed bones and fat.
Heat to boil.
Add grass.
Remove from heat.
Add bugs.
Cool and place on waxed paper to harden.
Eat and enjoy!

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat slightly in a little oil.
Add other ingredients until done (about 2 hours).
Thicken slightly with flour and water or cornstarch. Serve over cooked rice.

title: pear honey
directions: Put pears in food chopper (coarse).
Cook pears until clear, but not pink.
Add pineapple to pears.
Bring to a boil.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Process in water bath 15 minutes at low simmering temperature.

title: nacho dip
directions: Add desired amount of green pepper and onion to ground beef and cook until done.
Place refried beans in a quart casserole dish.
Place half of ground beef on top of beans.
Pour tomato sauce over beef.
Place remaining ground beef.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: mattie's pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter until smooth and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add all flavoring.
Add flour, alternating with milk until blended well.
Pour into a tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tests done.
Make a glaze from milk and powdered sugar and pour over cake while warm.

title: lima bean noodle cheese casserole
directions: Cook and cool lima beans; set to the side.
Cook noodles; put aside, then brown onion and garlic.
Brown hamburger, drain and add to onion and garlic.
Saute.
Mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix hamburger, onion and garlic, noodles, salt and pepper to your liking.
Then add lima beans.
Last add large can of tomato sauce, mix gently and layer shredded cheese all over top until covered. Place in oven at 325°
for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes until cheese is melted and casserole is good and hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: kraft salad stew or soup
directions: Put ingredients in pot and cook under slow fire.
Cook over 2 hours.
Add enough water to make stew and more water to make soup.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Layer chicken, then tortillas, chilies, onions and cheese in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together soup, milk, salt and pepper; pour 1/2 of soup mixture over all.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker dream bar
directions: Place 1 layer whole graham crackers on bottom of large pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Melt butter.
Add sugar, milk and egg.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture has come to full boil.
Add coconut, nuts and 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour over crust.
Add another layer of crackers.

title: butterscotch delicious
directions: Step 1:
Mix flour, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press thinly into buttered dish (3-quart oblong).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer in a baking dish (approximate size 7 x 11 x 4-inch) 1/2 can kraut, 1 cup bread cubes, 4 ounces dressing plus 1/4 cup water, 1 cup Swiss cheese and all of the corned beef.
Repeat second layer.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: quick chicken tortellini soup
directions: Heat broth.
Add chicken pieces.
Add spinach.
When broth begins to boil again, add tortellini.
Cook until al dente.
Salt and pepper to taste.
If it becomes too thick, add water or additional chicken broth.
When served with fresh Italian bread and fresh fruit cup, this soup makes a quick, nutritious winter meal.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Add jam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 2 times.
Add oil and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in grated carrots and chopped nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 300°.

title: staci's homemade oreos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine all ingredients except frosting until crumbly. Shape into nickel size balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 minutes. Remove and cool completely. Spread frosting between two cookies and make sandwich.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Add eggs and milk.	Beat until smooth.
Heat 1/4 inch of oil in a heavy skillet to 375 degrees.
Cover the bottom of a funnel with your finger and pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Hold funnel over hot oil and remove finger.	Move funnel in circular motion to form whatever design you want.
Fry for 2 minutes for until brown. Turn over and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or serve hot with syrup.
Repeat and repeat until everyone is stuffed.

title: no flour cookies
directions: Mix all together and let stand about 10 or 15 minutes to give oatmeal a chance to thicken.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine bread crumbs, milk, eggs and butter.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Turn into a greased loaf pan and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix fruit together in large bowl.
Sprinkle with pudding and Tang.
Stir and let set in fridge overnight.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Mix in lemon juice and mace.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in sour cream, add flour and beat at low speed.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter and spoon into a greased and floured (bottom only, both) 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: seafood jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Rinse under cold water. Invert on towel to cool.
Put tuna in a bowl.
Add cheese, mayo, celery and onion.
Add pimento.
If too dry, add more mayo.
Stuff shells; cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Garnish if desired.

title: italian style meat loaf(or meatballs)
directions: Mix all ingredients together (may add a tablespoon or so of water if desired) and shape into 2 loaves or meatballs as desired (may freeze part of this for future use).
Brown loaves or balls, then skim any excess fat.
Cover with your favorite meatless spaghetti sauce and cook in a moderate oven (350° to 375°) until done.

title: stuffed sweet peppers
directions: Cut tops out of peppers; take out seeds, then drop in hot water and allow to simmer for 10 minutes.
Plunge in cold water to harden.
Cook onion in butter a few minutes.
Add rest of the ingredients; mix well and cool.
Sprinkle peppers lightly with salt inside.
Stuff with mixture; bake in earthen dish until lightly browned.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Make up dough and roll out the size of a biscuit.
Put apples in dough, fill the pan.
Cover with sugar.
Add water up to the edge of dumplings.
Cook until apples are tender and top has browned some.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl beat eggs until thick. Gradually beat in sugar.
Combine melted butter (oleo) with flour, cocoa, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Add to egg-sugar mixture. Stir well with a spoon.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Immediately spread Marshmallow Creme gently on surface of cake.

title: caramel fudge icing
directions: Put all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly and bring to boil, with bubbling surface. Boil 2 minutes.
Cool until hand can be comfortably held on bottom of pan.
Stir in 2 cups powdered sugar (one at a time).
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla, and beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour over cake.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add tomatoes and cook until well mixed.
Prepare cornbread according to box directions and add corn to batter.
Pour half batter into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Top with meat and shredded cheese.
Pour remaining batter on top and spread more cheese to cover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until cornbread is golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: texas tacos
directions: Brown beef; drain off excess fat.
Add beans and tomatoes; simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over crushed Doritos and top with cheese, taco sauce, onions, lettuce and tomatoes in desired amounts.
Easy and fun to eat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce together until well blended. Place on bottom of pie pan.
Layer cheeses next.
Chop vegetables into small pieces and mix together.
Place on top of cheeses. Serve with nacho chips around pie pan.

title: turtle cake
directions: Unwrap caramel squares.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 of prepared mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, cook the salt pork until crisp. Add okra, which has been salted and peppered.
When okra is tender, add ham or chicken, tomatoes and gumbo file.
Simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp and cook until tender.
Adjust seasoning.
Serve over steaming hot rice.

title: mom's sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange layers of sliced, cooked sweet potatoes and broken walnuts in a shallow baking dish.
Make a sauce of brown sugar, orange juice and margarine.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Pour over sweet potatoes and bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and the taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Line bottom of a 2-quart flat casserole with 2 cups of corn chips.
Crush remaining corn chips and set aside.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Empty pie filling into shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir until blended.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients (flour and cocoa) alternately.
Stir in soda, salt, vanilla and food coloring; pour into greased and lined (wax paper) pans.
Makes three 9-inch layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use cream cheese frosting.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes, then pour over browned ribs, pork chops or chicken.
Bake slowly for 2 hours.

title: demp's pear relish
directions: Bring to boil. Simmer, covered, approximately 1 hour. Then can.

title: apple pudding
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place sliced apples 1/2 full.
Pour sugar and cinnamon over the top.
Mix topping:
brown sugar, melted butter and flour.
Pack on top of apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on the softness of the apples.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll biscuit out flat, then roll hot dog up in it.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° until brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Generously butter bottom and sides of a 3-quart elongated baking dish.
Pour asparagus evenly in bottom of baking dish. Grate or cut Cheddar cheese into very thin slices and place evenly on top of asparagus layer.
Cover with peas and pimento.
In a separate dish, dilute soup with milk and mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sour cream and mix together.
Pour over last vegetable layer.
Sprinkle with boiled eggs.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until dish is bubbly and crumbs slightly browned on top.
Makes 8 servings.
(Dish can be made a main dish by adding 2 cups chopped cooked chicken.)

title: pork chops and green beans
directions: Put green beans in baking dish with liquid from can.
Place pork chops on top.
Salt and pepper meat.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cover pan with foil while baking.

title: taco sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend for a few seconds. Place in a tight container in refrigerator.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: egg casserole
directions: Spread cheese in 8 x 8-inch dish and dot with butter.
Combine rest, except eggs.
Pour 1/2 over cheese, then add eggs; then add rest of the cream mixture.
You can add 1/2 cup ham, bacon, sausage, mushrooms, onions or any combination with the eggs.
Bake at 325° until set, about 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.
Can easily be doubled.

title: lemon bars
directions: Beat 1 egg and melted margarine together; mix in cake mix. Add pecans and mix well.
Put into a greased 10 x 15 pan.
Beat cream cheese, flavoring and sugar. Add one egg at a time.
Spread over crust. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in sour cream, egg, vanilla and nutmeg, mixing well until smooth.
Add apples.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 mintues.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: warm chocolate date cakes
directions: Butter six 3/4 c. custard cups.
Sprinkle dates and nuts in bottom of cups, dividing evenly.
In small saucepan, stir butter and chocolate over low heat until melted.
Cool.
Preheat oven to 375°.
With electric mixer beat eggs, egg yolks and sugar on high speed until light and fluffy, about 8-12 minutes.
Beat in flour gently.
Stir in chocolate mixture, liqueur and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour batter into cups and place on baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or until set around sides but soft in center.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run sharp knife around edges and invert onto platter. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna-goulash
directions: Brown the hamburg.
Mix the spaghetti sauce, hamburg and cheeses together.
If making the night before, mix noodles in uncooked.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sangria
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Stir in club soda.
Pour into glasses and top with orange slices if desired.
Makes 11 cups.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and chopped cherries.
Bake at 275° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 (8-inch) pans.
Cool.
Place one layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Add undrained pineapple, 2 sliced bananas, 1 1/2 cups prepared pudding and one container Cool Whip.
Place second layer of cake on top of Cool Whip.
Add thawed strawberries, 2 sliced bananas, 1 1/2 cups pudding and one container of Cool Whip. Cover with nuts and cherries.

title: ham tetrazzie
directions: Heat together and serve over cooked thin spaghetti.

title: brenda's biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and sugar together, then mix in the oil and buttermilk.
Prepare yeast as directed and mix in last.
Put in refrigerator and take out and use as much as you want each time.

title: baked parmesan fish fillets
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese and salt.
Dip fillets in combined egg and milk. Coat with crumb mixture. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: non-alcoholic punch
directions: Mix ingredients in a punch bowl and add ice ring with frozen strawberries.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp, then crumble.
Dice onion and fry in bacon grease.
Drain green beans, pinto beans and red beans.
Mix all together and bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes and uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Put into a large punch bowl and mix.
"That's all."

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
Layer tortillas, sauce and then cheese in large baking dish.
Top with cheese, then bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to temperature on pie crust; cook meat and drain. Add beans and mix (may add some of taco sauce).
Add 1/2 of meat to pie crust; put 1 layer of chips over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over meat; now add another layer of meat.
Sprinkle enough cheese on top to cover whole pie.
Let cook until brown; let cool 8 to 10 minutes.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and taco sauce to top of pie.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mock cheese souffle
directions: Trim all crust from bread.
Grate cheese.
Using large casserole, start with bread (broken up) and layer with cheese. Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Pour over bread and cheese.
May add a meat of your choice (ham or sausage).
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, put 1/4 stick oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash and dry potatoes.
Bake at 400° until crisp, about 45 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: orange scones
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and orange peel.
Cut in margarine (like pastry).
Add orange sections, milk and eggs. With fork, stir until mixture leaves side of bowl; will be gooey. Turn dough out on floured surface.
Knead 10 times.
Pour out in 6-inch circle on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cut in 8 wedges and separate a little bit. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: alice's country steak
directions: Mix flour, seasoning salt and pepper and pound into sides of meat.
(I prefer it cut into serving size pieces.)
Brown onion in 2 tablespoons shortening in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Remove; drain on paper toweling and set aside.
Add remaining shortening to skillet and brown meat slowly on both sides.
Add remaining ingredients; cover tightly and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Uncover and add browned onion; cover again and cook until tender, about 1 hour more.
Skim sauce to remove excess fat.
If sauce seems too thick, thin to desired consistency. Adjust seasoning to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate raspberry sauce
directions: Puree raspberries in blender or processor and strain.
In saucepan, whisk together cocoa and cream.
Add softened butter, sugar, syrup and raspberry liquid.
Blend and heat to boil, stir often, then let boil 8 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Cool and refrigerate.
May serve hot or cold over ice cream, cheese cake or pound cake.
Keeps at least one month.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare a 9-inch pie shell.
Brush it with the white of an egg and prick it well.
Put in oven until lightly brown.
Saute mushrooms with wine, garlic and bell pepper; cook and drain fat from bacon.
Scald to hasten cooking time the 2 cups cream.
Add to this pepper, nutmeg and salt.
Allow to cool slightly and beat together with 3 eggs.
Sprinkle in the bottom of the pie shell the bacon and Swiss cheese.
Pour the custard mixture over it and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until top is golden brown.
Test for doneness as for custard.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons of milk until smooth. Fold in half the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk; beat well. Combine flour and soda.
Add to mixture.
Blend.
Add vanilla. Chill 1 hour.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick.
Cut and place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar (optional). Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into 1 to 1 1/2-inch size balls.
Broil 10 to 12 minutes on a pan sprayed with Pam.
Serve in favorite sauce.

title: sauerbraten(germany)
directions: Combine vinegar, 1 cup water, 1/4 cup onion, bay leaves, paprika, cloves and thyme in saucepan.
Heat, do not boil.
Have meat in a shallow baking dish.
Pour vinegar mix over meat to cover.
Cover dish and store in refrigerator for at least 4 days, turning twice a day.
Remove meat and drain.
Save the marinade. Coat meat with flour and sear in hot oil.
Add the carrots, parsnips, celery and remaining onions.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour marinade over meat.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Remove meat and keep hot.

title: rice pudding(this pudding is very good.)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cinnamon, together, then place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: chicken and mushroom casserole
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken breasts and the vegetables.
Place the chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place the mushrooms, potatoes and carrots evenly on top of the chicken.
Dot the vegetables with the margarine.
Pour sherry or spoon cream of chicken soup over the chicken and vegetables.
Cover the dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade soup
directions: Combine all vegetables in a 10-quart pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until half done.
Add hamburger meat and tomato sauce.
Cover; cook on low heat.
Stir occasionally until done. Makes approximately 10 quarts.

title: easy kutnya
directions: Boil barley in salted water until tender.
Strain and rinse again with hot water.
Cool.
When ready to serve, pour honey, mixed with either poppy seed or nuts (or both) into barley.

title: orange cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese in bowl until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar, about 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in orange peel and juice, then food colorings, a small amount at a time, until orange (color will darken).
Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until firm enough to spread.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: chili cheese potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes until done.
Prepare as you always do with margarine, salt and pepper in a baking dish.
Heat chili in saucepan.
Put chili over baked potatoes.
Put all 3 cheeses over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted thoroughly.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat margarine and Coca-Cola to boiling point; pour over flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla, cocoa and marshmallows.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter in a large mixer bowl.
Combine powdered sugar and cocoa; add alternately with cream to cream cheese mixture.
Beat to spreading consistency.
Yields about 3 cups frosting.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and milk. Add butter to potatoes.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange cream pops
directions: You will need 10 plastic cups or popsicle molds (3 ounces each) and 10 popsicle sticks.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar and oil.
Add soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add carrots, pineapple, vanilla and flour.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: deep dish cottage pizza
directions: Prepare roll mix and let rise as directed on package.
Press on bottom and sides of greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
In skillet, cook sausage and garlic.
Pour off fat.
In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, tomato paste, onion, oregano and salt.
Spread in prepared pan.
Top with sausage, green pepper and grated cheese.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Add ground beef to water in a 4-quart pot.
Stir until beef separates to a fine texture.
Boil slowly for 1/2 hour.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir to blend, bringing to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for about 3 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, melt margarine and cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Lower heat and stir mixture to coat potatoes well.

title: creamed corn
directions: Blend together half & half, chicken bouillon cubes, pepper and sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add corn to boiling liquid, return to boil, reduce heat and simmer 3-5 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and water.
Add mashed bananas, flour, soda, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy cheesy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
In a shallow baking dish, shape half the mixture into loaf.
Cut 4 slices of cheese into strips; arrange on meat.
Top with remaining meat; press edges together to seal.
Bake for one hour.
Top with remaining cheese slices. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add lemon flavor, beaten egg yolks, flour, fruit and pecans.
Last, fold in egg whites.
Cook 2 hours at 225° in tube or loaf pans.

title: corn souffl{2e pudding
directions: Cook down corn,
pepper, onion, garlic, oil, pepper and salt. Stir constantly.
Fifteen
minutes	before serving, add egg and milk
previously
beaten
together.
Cook until thickened.

title: hester's buttermilk pie(recipe of my mother, rhoda messer)
directions: This
is easily made in a blender.
After blender mixes it for you, pour in pie shell on oven shelf.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 30 minutes or until filling is firm
and lightly browned on top.
Top usually cracks as it cools. Serves six.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil for 3 minutes and cool.
Dissolve soda, salt, artificial sweetener and water.
Add eggs; stir in flour, baking powder and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: puff-n-corn
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with tinfoil and lay corn out.
Mix sugar, syrup, and margarine and cook until boiling.
Take off stove and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn.
Preheat oven to 225° and bake 1/2 hour.
Mix it twice while in oven.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut bread in strips and toast.
Mix peanut butter, peanut oil and sugar.
Roll bread sticks in mixture, then roll in crushed graham crackers.
Spread on wax paper.

title: pineapple-cheese sauce
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and reserve.
Mix juice with flour and sugar.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Make alternate layers of pineapple, cheese and sauce.

title: kotlety
directions: Put meat into bowl.
Wet the bread with some milk, squeeze out excess mixture.
Add bread to meat, add slightly beaten eggs, onions, garlic, salt and pepper and mix well.
Turn onto a wet wooden bread board and form into small patties, oval shaped. Mixture should make about 12 cakes.
Dredge with bread crumbs on all sides, pressing to make the bread crumbs stick to the patties. Make a waffle pattern on the patty with a fork.
Heat Crisco in pan and cook the patties until brown.
Cook about 6 minutes on each side.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add combined dry ingredients alternately with the sour cream. Spread a little less than half of the batter into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle some of the sugar mixture and half of the nuts.
Add rest of the batter and rest of the sugar mixture and nuts. Dot with butter, if desired.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart saucepan; add brown sugar.
Mix well; remove from heat and let it cool (chips will melt if not cooled).
Add 1 egg at a time and mix well.
Add nuts and chips. Add flour and mix well.
Place mixture in large oblong pan, at least 9 x 13-inch or slightly larger.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars; remove from pan.

title: clafoutis limousin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, eggs, milk and salt.
Beat well.
Batter will be thin.
In a greased 10-inch round pan, place fruit (example: 12 ounces frozen blueberries and 16 ounce can drained peaches). Sprinkle brandy over fruit.
Carefully pour batter over fruit.
Dot with butter and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on fruit.
Cool before serving.

title: grandmother's cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter skillet fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or a 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan; put sugar, milk and butter in frying pan.
Turn up to 280°.
Mix until starting to boil.
Continue stirring while boiling for 5 minutes. Mixture will turn brownish.
Turn off frying pan.
Add rest of ingredients quickly.
Mix together until well blended and mixture sugars.
Pour into pan, scraping frying pan well.
Allow to cool. Cut into 16 to 25 pieces.
Savor those crumbs, too!

title: cheese stuffed bell peppers
directions: Set cooked rice aside. Boil peppers in salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Saute ground beef and onion.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1/4 cup water.
Add to meat mixture.
Mix rice and tomatoes and add to meat mixture. Mix rice and tomatoes and add to meat.
Stir thoroughly and stuff mixture into green peppers. Place peppers in greased baking dish.

title: date muffins
directions: Bring chopped dates, water and soda to a boil.
Let cool. Cream oleo and sugar; add to cooled date mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients at low speed or by hand until well mixed; do not overbeat.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Drain the cooked spinach.
Mix with other ingredients and put in buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and dots of butter. Bake, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Mix egg and apples.
Blend all together.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Cover with another pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yeast corn bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle yeast in. Stir in milk mixture, eggs, flour and corn meal.
Beat until well blended.
Batter will be stiff.
Turn into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place, free from draft, until double in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: easy oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Add oil to shallow baking pan.
Place flour and seasonings in small paper sack or plastic bag.
Drop in 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time.
Shake sack.
Place floured chicken, skin side down.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn skin side up and continue the baking about 30 minutes until tender and crispy.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (hands work best).
Put in 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°, covered. Uncover and brown.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Melt the marshmallows in 1/2 cup milk in a double boiler. Stir in the green creme de menthe and the white creme de menthe. Fold in whipped cream.
Crunch Oreos in blender.
Add melted butter.
Press into an 8-inch pie plate.
Add marshmallow mixture and freeze. Take out 20 minutes before serving.

title: golden kolacky(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Gradually add flour.
Blend until soft dough forms. Divide dough in half; wrap each in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until firm.
Roll out dough 1/2 at a time on floured surface to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Spoon 1 teaspoon preserves in center of each square.
Bring up to opposite corners and pinch together then fold pinch to one side.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove and cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and seasoning; stir until smooth.
Slowly add the hot milk, stirring constantly.
When it thickens, melt the cheese in the sauce.
Into a greased 2-quart casserole dish, put layers of sliced potatoes and cheese sauce, alternating until all ingredients are used.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna pasta
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer a few minutes.
Set aside.
Cook tuna in a nonstick skillet about 10 minutes.
Add to sauce mixture; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: vegi liver
directions: Slice vegetables.
Cut liver in small pieces.
Add all ingredients together.
Heat oil until hot.
Fry everything together.
When liver is tender, take out of oil.
Drain on paper.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells.
Brown meat with seasonings; cool.
Mix together eggs and cheeses; add cooled meat.
Stuff into shells and arrange in baking dish.
Pour sauce over shells.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked french toast
directions: Lightly coat 13 x 9 pan with cooking spray.
Arrange bread in bottom of pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour evenly over bread.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bread with cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with hot maple syrup, powdered sugar and cinnamon.

title: cooked mayonnaise
directions: Mix the sugar and eggs together.
Then mix the cornstarch and water together, along with the vinegar, then the salt.
Cook all the ingredients in a saucepan until it is thickened. Add the butter after it is cooked.
This makes about 1 pint.

title: sausage lasagne wrap
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Divide sausage into 6 pieces.
Split lengthwise and stuff with one slice of Mozzarella cheese. Wrap each piece in noodle.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with sauce and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle a little Parmesan cheese over and serve.

title: jambalaya
directions: Make roux (shortening or oil and flour).
Brown over a low heat.
Add celery, green pepper and onion to roux.
Saute.
Chop meat into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in a small amount of fat.
Add to ingredients that are sauteed in roux.
Add rice.
Add 2 cups of water to a cup of rice.
Add seasonings and cook over medium heat until rice is done.

title: old orchard fruit dessert
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish with the fruit.
Sprinkle with one cup of sugar and a few drops of almond extract.
Mix the remaining cup of sugar with the flour and margarine.
Stir in one egg.
The mixture will be sticky.
Drop the mixture on the fruit and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: meat spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in oil; add meat and brown. Add tomatoes, chili powder and water. Cover and cook over slow heat for 30 minutes. Add mushrooms, peas, corn, salt and pepper. Add cooked spaghetti to sauce and blend well. Fill large greased baking dish half full; cover with 1/2 cheese. Add the remaining meat and spaghetti and top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve
jello in 1/2 cup of very hot water.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 to 3 tablespoons of cold water.
Add all ingredients to cold jello mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Original recipe.

title: caramel nut cake
directions: Cream
butter,
sugar
and
Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat
well.
Sift
flour
in bowl and add baking powder and salt. Add to butter mixture and alternate with milk.
Add vanilla.
Coat nuts with a little of flour mixture and stir in last.
Put
in well-greased
funnel
pan.
Put cake in a cold oven.
Cook
for
1 hour and 40 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Wait 10 minutes and turn out.

title: vegie and cheese frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam vegetable about 4 minutes.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until softened.
Stir in vegetables. In bowl, fold vegetables into eggs, dressing and bread crumbs. Pour into buttered quiche dish.
Sprinkle top with cheeses.
Bake for 25 minutes or until eggs set.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Blend cooking oil, sugar and eggs in mixer.
Add apples and nuts.
Sift in salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add vanilla and flour. Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into an ungreased 10 x 14-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with whipped topping, if desired.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine crumbs with the seasonings and butter.
Add milk, liquid and oil from salmon and slightly beaten eggs.
Mix well. Flake the salmon and add to the mixture.
Pour into oiled baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until firm and browned.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine in a saucepan and heat over medium, stirring to help bits to melt.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 3 1/2 cups of delicious sauce.

title: fruit punch for 100
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Let stand for an hour.
Before serving, add ginger ale and ice.

title: spicy peach nut bread
directions: Split pita bread.
Butter bread.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and dill. Cut in 1 1/2-inch slices. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes until butter is melted.

title: lemon chicken stir-fry(4 one cup servings)
directions: In a small bowl, stir together chicken broth, soy sauce, lemon juice, sugar and cornstarch; set aside.
Heat vegetable oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add carrots and stir-fry 30 to 40 seconds.
Add snow peas and garlic; stir-fry an additional 30 seconds.
Remove vegetables from skillet with slotted spoon; set aside.
Add chicken strips and cook, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes or until no longer pink.
Add reserved broth mixture. Bring to boil and cook until thickened.
Stir in green onion and reserved vegetable mixture.
Heat until hot.
Serve over rice.

title: southern lady cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 12-cup tube pan with cooking spray or grease and dust with flour.
In a large mixing bowl of an electric mixer, combine the cake mix, sugar and flour, then add the sour cream, vegetable oil and orange extract, mixing at low speed. Add eggs one at a time.
Increase speed to medium and beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in the mandarin oranges until they are well distributed.
Pour batter into the prepared tube pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tester inserted comes out clean.
When done, remove the cake from the oven and allow to cool in the pan for about 15 minutes.
Then invert the cooled cake onto a plate or wire rack.

title: pound cake(euna edwards')
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until light at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each. Add flour and mix well (with slow speed). Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2
hours.

title: shrimply delicious dip
directions: Mix all together.
Mix ahead and refrigerate.
Serve with chips.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Let cut up rind stand in salted water (to cover) overnight. (Use 2 tablespoons salt to 1 quart of water.)
Next day, drain. Cover with fresh cold water.
Cook until tender.
Drain.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into bowl.
Beat eggs slightly in small bowl.
Stir in milk and butter.
Pour mixture over dry ingredients and stir until just blended.
(Batter will be lumpy.
Overbeating will make a tough cake.)
Bake in lightly greased frying pan or griddle and serve at once.

title: chicken rose
directions: "Need chicken for 4 to 6 people."
Mix together.
Place chicken in casserole dish; pour mixture over.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Serve with wild and long grain rice.

title: crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan(s).
Do not flour.
Sift dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes in dry mixture.
In first hole, pour oil; in second hole, pour vinegar; in third hole, pour vanilla. Pour ice water over all.
Stir with fork until evenly blended. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° layer or sheet cake only.
Will not do well in Bundt pan.

title: raspberry-topped lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch; cook and stir until mixture thickens and is clear.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Put tomatoes and onions in blender and blend well.
Pour through a colander to remove seeds and skins.
Boil tomato mixture until thick (about 1 hour).
Add remaining ingredients and cook until desired thickness is reached.
Seal in 6 pint jars.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar, eggs and mashed bananas.
Beat well.
Stir in buttermilk.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan (spray with Pam spray).
Let stand 20 minutes before putting into oven.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar on low; heat in cake pan or skillet.
Place pineapple slices and cherries in bottom of pan. Combine dry ingredients alternately with pineapple juice until well blended and pour over pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 9 or 10-inch cake.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in very large bowl.
This will make 2 pans full of dressing.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Can be kept for several weeks.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix sour cream, onion soup mix and minced clams. Add a little clam juice to thin mixture to desired consistency.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: memaw's banana pudding
directions: In baking dish, put a layer of vanilla wafers, a layer of bananas and repeat.

title: johnson's temptation
directions: Fry onions in butter or oil. Place potatoes in bottom of oiled 9 x 13-inch pan. Be sure to cover bottom. Layer onions on top to cover potatoes. Next, layer herring. Continue layering until top of pan is reached. Place in a 200° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove pan from oven and pour in cream. Cover with foil and bake an additional 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are cooked through.

title: spanish rice and beef
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Saute bacon in skillet until done.
Brown onions in 1/2 the bacon fat.
Cook ground beef and salt until beef is grey in color.
Add tomatoes, well-washed rice, bacon and paprika.
Turn into greased casserole.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.
Add hot water if needed during cooking.
Makes 5 servings.

title: festive freeze pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream at medium speed in electric mixer until well blended.
Add sherbet; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into chocolate crumb pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Dissolve coffee in 1 tablespoon hot water.
In a large bowl, beat all ingredients with an electric mixer at medium speed until frosting holds stiff peaks.
Great on white cake.

title: hush puppies for 100
directions: Blend flour, cornmeal, milk, baking powder and salt in a very large bowl.
Combine eggs and water; add to mixer bowl.
Add onions and pepper.
Add shortening and drop batter by rounded tablespoonful into deep 360° fat.
Fry about 3 minutes.
Yield: 300 Hush Puppies.

title: corn casserole
directions: You will need a 2-quart casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch dish, greased.

title: cola-basted southern ham
directions: Place ham, fat side down, in roasting pan.
Add cola to half cover ham.
Bake at 350°, allowing 15 minutes per pound.
Baste ham frequently with cola.
Remove ham from pan.
Skin it and rub well with brown sugar, pepper, bread crumbs and dry mustard. Press coating into ham.
Place ham on rack; return to oven and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer, occasionally basting with cola.

title: date swirl cookies
directions: Cook together dates, water and 1/4 cup sugar for 5 minutes, then add the walnuts.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugars together thoroughly.
Add well beaten egg.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Put on slightly floured board and roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread date mixture on dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 400°.

title: vegetable chili(low-fat "spa" recipe)
directions: Combine onions and 1/4 cup broth in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat until onion is wilted, 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic, chili powder, cumin and oregano.
Cook 1 more minute.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Chop celery and cabbage.
Brown hamburg.
Add celery, garlic and tomatoes.
One or 2 quarts of tomatoes can be used, but add equal amounts of water.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in mixture; add kidney beans, with juice.
Season with pepper; add cabbage.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix together mustard and jelly.
Heat until dissolved.
Then add wieners.
Simmer for exactly 1 hour on low heat.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Pour in milk and mix.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll into balls and shape into strawberries.
Roll sides in red sugar.
Put almonds in small plastic bag with green food coloring and shake until almonds are coated.
Dip top of strawberry in green sugar and insert almond stem.
This recipe makes approximately 40 strawberries, if they are not too large.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage in bottom of greased baking dish.
Spread sliced onion on cabbage, then spread celery on onion. Pour undiluted celery soup over mixture.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: old fashion chocolate fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and nuts, in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to a low setting and cook, stirring occasionally, to 235° or until mixture forms a soft ball in water, about 3 hours.
Remove from heat and let stand until cool.
Add vanilla and stir until it becomes thick and creamy.
Add nuts. Pour into small greased dish. Mark into squares.
Top each square with nut half.
Makes 1 pound.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Put evaporated milk into freezer for 1/2 hour or more.
Mix jello and hot water.
Mix to dissolve.
Let jell, but not too firm. Melt oleo.
Crush graham crackers (put a little aside for topping). Mix oleo and crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
In bowl mix cream cheese, sugar, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
In large bowl beat the evaporated milk, it will double in volume.
Beat in cream cheese mixture.
Beat jello separately until well broken up.
Add to cream cheese mixture. Pour over cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or more.

title: grandma's baked spaghetti
directions: Cut bacon into small 1-inch pieces and fry with chopped onion until well cooked, but not crisp; drain off grease.
Cook spaghetti; drain and place in greased dish.
Add bacon, onion and stewed tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
If dish appears too dry, you can add tomato juice or tomato paste.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: king size cheesy corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease king size muffin pan.
In large bowl, combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
In a medium bowl, whisk together eggs, sour cream and oil until smooth.
Add corn, cheese and chiles.
Add this mixture to dry ingredients and mix well.
Divide batter evenly into muffin cups. Bake 25 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 to 10 minutes before removing.

title: grandma greiner's spice cake
directions: Boil first 8 ingredients 3 minutes.
Cool completely (I usually do it overnight).
Add last 2 ingredients.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes, until pulls away from sides of pan.
Makes 2 (one-layer) cakes.
(Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.)

title: ratatouille rice
directions: Cook and stir onion and zucchini in hot oil in skillet until tender.
Add tomatoes and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and cheese; cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender until well blended. Refrigerate.
Makes a blender full.
Add to coffee or mix with cream.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken with garlic, onion and celery salts, salt and pepper until tender.
Debone chicken and cut in bite size pieces. Spread evenly on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Place browned and drained sausage in bottom of casserole dish. Add chopped vegetables.
Mix rice, soup and water; pour over top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: baked supreme zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Place chopped bacon, onion and tomatoes in hollows.
Season to taste. Place in 9-inch cake pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut each half zucchini in half and serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix.
Add salad dressing to whatever consistency you desire.

title: spicy fruit compote(microwave recipe)
directions: Drain cherries, apple rings, peaches, pineapple chunks and apricots.
Cut apple rings in thirds and peaches in half.
In 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf dish, gently toss fruits with sugar, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Cover dish with plastic wrap, turning back one corner to vent.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes on High in microwave.

title: fisherman's wharf salad
directions: Cook rice as directed and chill.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Makes nice stuffed tomatoes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; drain off excess fat.
Add next four ingredients.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add small amounts of water if necessary.
Salt to taste.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender, following package instructions.
Drain, rinse in cold water.
Place 1/3 of noodles in 9 X 13 baking dish; cover with 1/3 of sauce, then layer 1/2 of Mozzarella and 1/2 of cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Can be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: sweet stickles
directions: Peel
cucumbers,
cut lengthwise and scoop out the seed with spoon.
Cut
into
strips
the size of your finger.
Soak cucumbers overnight in lime and water.

title: rice-vegetable pilaf
directions: Combine water and bouillon granules in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add rice; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand covered 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, carrots, parsley, green onions and pepper.
Stir well.
Place over low heat; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Serves 8.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Mix Jell-O well by directions on Jell-O box, but less 1/4 cup water.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
When Jell-O begins to thicken, add drained pineapple (reserve juice).
Let congeal.

title: lazy cabbage roll casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased 2-quart casserole.
Brown together hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Add rice, soup and water; mix. Heat through, about 10 minutes.
Then pour over cabbage.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is tender at 325°.
So easy to fix!

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat red hots and water until red hots are melted.
Add Jell-O to this mixture while it is hot.
Let partially cool.
Add 2 cups applesauce.
Pour into dish or mold and refrigerate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press and spread crescent roll dough on pizza pan.
Pour sausage over dough and cover with grated cheese.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add desired amount of salt, pepper and oregano and pour mixture over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate cookies (no bake)
directions: Spread each flat side of 18 Ritz crackers with peanut butter; press another cracker on top.
Do all 18.
Place chocolate bark in pan (cut squares to melt faster).
Put over low heat or melt in microwave.
Stir until smooth.
Use tongs and dip crackers in melted chocolate.
Place on sheet of foil.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and flour, alternating and beating between each addition.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a small tube pan.

title: easy stew
directions: Cut meat into bite size portions.
Brown well in oil.
Drain off excess oil and add water and soup mix.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour, adding small amounts of water as needed to maintain level.
Add tomato sauce and continue simmering another hour.
Add potatoes and when almost done, add remaining vegetables.
Continue cooking until potatoes are done.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine beef, salt, sugar, tomato sauce, garlic and pepper. Cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese and mix with noodles.
In a greased 3-quart casserole, alternate layers of meat mixture, cheese and noodle mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
If desired, a 1 pound can of tomatoes may be substituted for 2 cups tomato sauce.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix drained Veg-All, mayonnaise and onion in a casserole dish. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with grated cheese.
Top the cheese with crushed crackers.
Pour butter over the top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large frypan, brown the meat; drain. Stir in dry taco seasoning mix. Chill.
In a large salad bowl, mix the lettuce, kidney beans, tomato, celery and onion. When ready to serve, add meat, Catalina and Italian dressings and Doritos.
Makes 6 hearty main dishes or 24 side dish servings.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots until done.
Drain and cool.
Combine all other ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Pour over cooked carrots. Mix together.
Let set overnight.

title: moravian sugar cake(recipe from bethlehem, pennsylvania)
directions: Boil potatoes; reserve 1 cup of water.
Cream salt, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add 1 cup of potatoes. Add 2 cups flour to potato mixture and mix in; add remaining 2 cups flour (do not mix).
Dissolve 1 1/2 envelopes dry yeast in lukewarm potato water.
This may be done before mixing main ingredients. Pour yeast potato water mixture into flour mixture and blend with hands.
It will be very sticky.
Place in 2 or 3 greased 9-inch pans or 1 (9-inch) and 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Dough should be approximately 3/4-inch thick.
Let rise in a warm place 3 to 4 hours or longer, depending on your house temperature.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle heavily with light brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown. Best when served warm.

title: bacon-cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and cut cauliflower in flowerets.
Break lettuce into small pieces.
Add bacon, cheese and mayonnaise; mix well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In an oblong baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch), layer as follows: sliced zucchini, sauteed onion, celery, green pepper and garlic (and add salt and Italian seasoning to this), Stove Top dressing (prepared as directed; save a few crumbs for top) and cream of mushroom soup and sour cream mixed together.
Sprinkle with reserved Stove Top dressing.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: heath candy bars
directions: Cook brown sugar and butter until hard crack.
Put nuts into greased pan.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Immediately cover with milk chocolate chips.
Candy will break in pieces.

title: date rolls
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients on low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour over Rice Krispies and walnuts.
Cool.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.

title: beef tips or deer steak
directions: Put into slow cooker and cook all day.
That night put over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: birthday cake icing
directions: In a large mixer, mix sugar and Crisco.
Slowly add water until creamy and smooth.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
If too thick, add water, drop by drop.
Great to use with tube and tips for decorating or just spread on cake or cupcakes.
May be colored with food coloring too.

title: pasta with olive oil and garlic
directions: Boil spaghetti al dente.
In pan of hot oil, cook red hot flaked red pepper to quick boil.
Add 1 tablespoon of water. Drain spaghetti and mix into oil with pepper in pan.
Then mix with chopped watercress or rugulla.
Serve hot immediately.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Chop rhubarb into cubes, add sugar and mix well.
Let set for 30 minutes to an hour.
Beat eggs, flour, vanilla and milk.
Add mixture to rhubarb and sugar.
Stir well and pour into a 9 inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pear preserves cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then add vanilla and spices.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and buttermilk. Mix, then add pear preserves and pecans.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: saucy alligator casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large size skillet.
Add alligator to skillet in 1-inch pieces.
Brown lightly.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery.
Saute vegetables until tender-crisp.
Add garlic powder, salt and black pepper.
Mix well.
Add rice and salsa; stir until well blended.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix cracker crumbs with 1/4 cup butter and spread over top of casserole.
Bake 20 minutes in oven at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat the egg yolks, adding the sugar slowly.
Pour in the whiskey very gradually, then add rum.
Stir in the milk, then cream.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: taco shells
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour about 3 tablespoons into medium hot pan.
Roll pan around until bottom is covered.
Flip over 1 time.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Wash and peel shrimp.
Put on skewer.
Sprinkle lemon pepper over shrimp.
Mix butter, garlic powder, lemon juice, water and Worcestershire sauce and bring to a good boil.
Put shrimp on grill and marinade with sauce for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Let cheese stand to room temperature. Rinse mushrooms. With teaspoon, fill each mushroom with cheese spread. Spray 9 x 9 baking pan with cooking spray. Place stuffed mushrooms in pan and cook for approximately 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven until bubbly. Quick, easy and good.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Butter a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Start with first ingredients, keep mixing after each one.
Mix for 15 minutes for lighter cake.
Bake at 325°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in pan of water. When cooked, open oven door and let cool in oven.
Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.
Serve with cherries, pineapple, etc.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients on slow speed until well blended.
Add the buttermilk and mix.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: cheesanchokes
directions: Mix together.
Place in shallow dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with spreader and crackers.
Eat and gain!

title: marinade(for 16 to 20 chops, beef or chicken or kabobs)
directions: Mix in a bowl.
Add meat; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or less, depends on quantity of meat you are marinating.
Grill.

title: our favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream, flour and soda. Fold in beaten egg whites (stiff, but not dry), lemon extract and vanilla.
Bake in greased, lightly floured tube pan in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until well done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Blend flour and shortening together.
Add water, egg and vinegar if desired.
Roll out flat and spread with margarine and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: blueberry peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, oil and milk, stirring until mixture forms a soft pastry dough. Place in 9-inch deep dish pie pan, pressing dough evenly over bottom and sides.
Combine confectioners sugar, 1/3 cup flour, blueberries and peaches; spoon over pastry.
Combine 3/4 cup flour, brown sugar and cinnamon; cut in butter until crumbly. Spread evenly over fruit.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned bread pudding(this is easy to make.)
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Drizzle butter into an 8-inch square pan.
Whisk together sugar and next three ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in bread; spoon mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; stir.
Bake 35 more minutes or until pudding is set.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix well; pour in greased 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix and roll into golf size balls.

title: rolls
directions: Mix and knead.
Let rise 1 1/2 or 2 hours.
Roll and cut out. Place on greased pan.
Brush with margarine and let rise again. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: mocha coffee
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Store in closed container.
Stir 1 or more teaspoons into cup of hot water.

title: fruit salad
directions: All ingredients, except bananas, can be done ahead.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: spud's dog biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients except water.
Mix in just enough water to make stiff dough. Let stand 10 minutes.
Form 30 balls, then flatten to bone shape.
Microwave 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender and drain.
Place in casserole dish with stems down.
Combine sour cream, cheese, bouillon and mustard.
Spoon it over the cauliflower.
Melt margarine.
Stir in bread crumbs, walnuts, dill and onion salt.
Sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven 375°.
Grease 9 x 13 baking pan.
Cook beef and onion in a skillet until done; drain.
Stir in taco sauce, water, chiles and seasoning mix; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook stirring occasionally for 3 to 4 minutes.
Layer half of shells on the bottom of baking dish; cover with half of meat mixture, sprinkle with one cup of cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Top with garnish.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain the pork and beans.
Let sit while you mix the rest of the ingredients in large bowl.
Add beans and stir.
Simmer in crock-pot on low setting for 2 to 3 hours for best results.

title: dip ala sandtrap
directions: Cream the cheeses with an electric mixer, add the spices and blend in the finely diced vegetables with a wooden spoon.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken salad(serves 4)
directions: Boil chicken and cool.
Take meat off bones and chop.
Add grapes at last minute, if you "do ahead."
Serve over lettuce and garnish with tomato wedges, etc.

title: sweet potatoes and pineapple
directions: Peel and dice sweet potatoes.
Cook until a little "boney," not quite tender.
Add the crushed pineapple.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Add the brown sugar.
Bake at 350° until tender and glazed.

title: hot sauce
directions: Place in food processor all ingredients, chopped in small pieces.
Blend to your liking, chunky or smooth; salt and pepper to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: venison cordon bleu
directions: Flatten steaks to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top each steak with a slice of cheese, and a slice of ham. Roll up tight.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and margarine well.
Roll out into a rectangle.
May need extra Bisquick or flour to prevent sticking. Top with sausage and grated cheese.
Roll up as a jelly roll. Wrap in aluminum foil.
Freeze.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine juice and orange rind, shortening and enough boiling water to make a total of 3/4 cup. Add egg.
Blend liquid into dry ingredients, stir only until flour mixture is dampened.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Push batter up into corners of pan, leaving the center slightly hollowed.
For well rounded loaf, allow batter to stand in pan for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: banana loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and then fold in bananas and nuts. Bake in loaf pan 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: low calorie soup
directions: Boil barley and peas for 8 minutes.
Add all vegetables except zucchini and boil.
Add zucchini and simmer until ready to eat.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon; remove skin and bones.
Combine salmon with next five ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours. Combine parsley and pecans.
Shape salmon mixture into a log and roll into pecan and parsley mixture.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers.
Wonderful!

title: salsa
directions: Dice chilis, scallions and tomatoes; mix together.
Finely chop cilantro and garlic.
I use a food processor.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add lemon juice, tomato sauce and salt.
Then mix. If salsa is too hot, add more tomatoes and it will cool down without ruining the taste.
When using the cilantro, use only the leaves and use what tastes good to you.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown onion in oleo.
Add meat and garlic.
Brown.
Stir flour into broth and cook thoroughly.
Add sauerkraut and parsley. Put in bowl and chill until workable.
Form into balls.
Mix together egg and milk.
Dip balls into egg mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until browned.
Deep fry at 300° for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: granny's peanut butter cake
directions: Add all ingredients except peanut butter.
Cook while stirring to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter and stir well.

title: pink lemonade icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly with a spoon.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and chill 1 hour.

title: erica's orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Serve at once.
If made ahead, may keep in freezer, then reblend!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Add water, oil, nuts, eggs and pumpkin; mix well. Pour into three greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour (or more) at 350° (325° for glass pans).

title: taco chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger with green pepper.
Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients into hamburger mixture and simmer over low heat until warm and well blended.
Serve warm with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: wonderful cheese grits
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add 1/2 cup margarine and stir in grits.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture is the consistency of oatmeal (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat, add salt and pepper and beat mixture well with eggbeater.
Add the 1/3 cup margarine, stir in Swiss cheese and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This can be made the day before and cooked when ready to serve.
The cheeses give this dish a unique taste.
Compliments game beautifully.
Serves 10.

title: microwave easy gravy
directions: Pour drippings into 4 cup glass measure.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Pour in liquid and stir briskly until well blended.
Cook on High 3 to 4 minutes or until boiling, stirring several times during cooking.
Season with salt and pepper. Beat until smooth. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: fred's salad
directions: Prepare lettuce and cauliflower as for a salad.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower, peas and onion.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese and bacon.
Then spread mayonnaise over the top of the salad.
Cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Toss well before serving.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Reserve 3 cups.
Spread and pack the remaining sugar-nut mixture in the bottom of a greased and floured 10 x 14-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. While this mixture is baking, combine all other ingredients, medium speed, with an electric mixer.
Pour mixture over the hot crust when removed from oven.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top and return cake pan to oven.
Bake for an additional 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares!

title: mahogany cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and sift again with salt and soda. Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sifted ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture while beating on low speed.
Add melted chocolate and blend well.
Bake in two 8 or 9-inch round, greased pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Jell-O together. Pour 1 cup of hot water over. You may use the juice from the fruit cocktail as well. Mix with mixer. Add cocktail. Add nuts and celery. Mix well. Cover with marshmallows and refrigerate.

title: overnight black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Toss with vegetables and toothpicked garlic to coat lightly.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Remove toothpicked garlic before serving.

title: hot chicken, turkey salad pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Top with crushed potato chips and grated cheese.
Bake at 500° until cheese melts. Serve hot or cold.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat, onion, peppers, chili powder, salt and pepper. Drain.
Add corn.
Mix corn bread mix and add to meat mixture. Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ranch style dip
directions: Place cottage cheese in container of blender; process until smooth.
Add sour cream and remaining ingredients.
Process until blended.
May have to stop and scrape the sides occasionally. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Slice apples in small bowl; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Grease tube pan, then pour in 1/2 of the batter, then 1/2 of the sliced apples.
Repeat with batter and apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or longer. Do not be alarmed; cake will be very brown on outside.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, onion soup mix, beef, egg and crumbs. Shape.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Spoon off fat, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Combine remaining soup, water and drippings; heat. Add tomato sauce if desired.
Pour over meat loaf and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, put potatoes, hot water, sugar, shortening and salt.
