When cool, add eggs, yeast and flour a little at a time to make a soft dough. Knead until smooth; put in greased bowl and cover with waxed paper.
Set in refrigerator (as this rises in refrigerator).
Let set several hours or overnight.
The dough wants to be a little on the sticky side.
Make into rolls or buns (or whatever).
Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
This dough will keep in the refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.

title: anna's crab cakes
directions: Pick over crab meat but leave as large as possible.
Meanwhile have bread soaking in milk.
Squeeze milk from bread, breaking in pieces.
Add to crab meat with eggs, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Mix lightly.
Press into cakes.
Place on lightly floured paper or plate.
Sprinkle with enough flour, for easy handling.
Fry in fat (butter) until deep brown on both sides.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Place strawberries and Equal in a food processor or blender. Mix until coarsely chopped.
With motor running, gradually add evaporated milk.
Mix until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4. This looks pretty served in tall parfait glasses.
Low-fat, .2 g fat; 167 calories.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place cleaned chicken in cooker.
Pour catsup and Coca-Cola over chicken.
Cook on low about 6 hours.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour once before measuring, then sift with soda and salt.
Cream shortening until soft.
Add sugars gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients.
Add nut meats and chocolate, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by half teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Makes 100.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Mix above ingredients together. Bake in muffin pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creole sauce
directions: Melt butter, add onion and green pepper, and blend in the flour.
Gradually stir in tomatoes and bay leaf.
Cook until it thickens.
Add olives.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix eggs and milk together, then add flour, sugar and cocoa. Put in microwave for about 6 minutes, stirring halfway through. Add margarine after you take out of microwave.
Beat it if necessary.
May be served warm or cool.

title: asparagus-chicken casserole
directions: Layer as listed in greased casserole.
Top with little more shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes. Cut into large chunks.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over potatoes. Toss until well covered.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: classic waffles
directions: Beat yolks, add oil and milk. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add all the liquid mixture to flour, etc. and beat only until moistened.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in milk over
low
heat.	Stir in pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered wax paper.
Chill.

title: chili bacon bites
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Cut bacon slices in halves.
Wrap each half around a chunk of pineapple.
Assemble on skewers alternating pineapple/bacon with olive.
Blend pineapple juice with chili sauce; brush on skewers and broil.
Use remaining chili sauce as a dunk.

title: pauley's poulet
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt, pepper and onion salt.
Remove meat from bones and cut into pieces.
Cook broccoli until tender in remaining chicken broth.
Drain well.
Arrange broccoli in bottom of 3-quart Pyrex dish (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch).
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine cream of chicken soup with mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
Can be made before and refrigerated.
I use more curry powder than called for.

title: hot pepper rings
directions: Cut peppers in rings.
Place pepper rings in pan with above ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Spoon into jars.
Seal.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place apple pie filling in greased 1-quart baking dish. Combine all remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Great with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in sprayed pan according to cornbread mix directions.

title: quesadilla
directions: Spread cheeses evenly on half of the flour tortilla.
Top with green chilies and green onion.
Fold the tortilla in half and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven, turning once, until both sides of the tortilla are browned and cheeses are melted.
Cut into wedge shapes and serve with picante sauce, sour cream and guacamole for dipping.
Makes 1 serving.

title: raisin bars
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil; stir in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until tests done with toothpick.

title: butterfinger candy bar dessert
directions: Mix melted oleo with soda cracker and graham cracker crumbs. Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save a few crumbs for topping.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream and pour on top of crumbs.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Crush candy bars and nuts.
Mix with remaining crumbs and sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel, then shred into large bowl.
Stir in sour cream, onion, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and sprinkle with paprika.

title: sausage bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Thaw dough and stretch out about 12-inches.
Be careful not to put holes in dough.
Spread with sausage.
Top with remaining ingredients except egg white and seed.
Roll dough up tightly like a jelly roll.
Tuck ends under and place on cookie sheet with open end down.
Brush with egg white and work egg white into ends to seal. Sprinkle with seed.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: meat ham loaf
directions: Mix into a loaf.
Baste with basting sauce.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar in pan and boil.
Remove from heat; add jello and mix well.
Pour over popcorn.
Mixing well, form into balls.

title: saucy tuna bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and seasonings.
Stir in remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Turn into shallow 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 5 to 10 minutes more or until bubbly at edges.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Add frozen berries. Chill to partially set the jello.
Blend together the cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread cheese mixture over bottom of shell, then spread raspberry mixture on the cheese.
Chill until set.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Add flour; stir quickly to blend.
Cook over low heat until smooth. Add milk.
Cook, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Add remaining 4 cups chicken stock and the cubed chicken.
Continue cooking until heated through.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Makes 8 servings.

title: messy chicken
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together and coat chicken pieces.
Place in greased, shallow baking dish and bake at 400 F for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with each can of soup. Place in oven and bake until done, approximately 30-45 minutes.

title: danish rice pudding
directions: To Make Pudding:
In medium saucepan, heat sugar, water, gelatin and salt, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved, about 1 minute.
Stir in milk, rice and vanilla.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Blend together mayonnaise, salt and marjoram.
Add to chicken mixture. Toss together lightly to coat all ingredients.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water; drain.
Season with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in soup, sour cream and pimento.
Combine 1/2 cup butter and stuffing mix, stirring until well blended.
Combine half of stuffing mixture and all of squash mixture.
Put into a 2-quart buttered casserole. Put remaining stuffing mix on top and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May use a mixture of brown sugar, melted butter and nuts for a crunchy topping.

title: shrimp newberg
directions: Mix butter, flour and cream, then add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Add shrimp and sherry. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
To serve:
Heat in double boiler about 45 minutes.

title: cherry chip pie
directions: Let yogurt soften slightly.
Place yogurt into pie shell, then layer remaining ingredients.
Only use 1/2 jar of fudge topping and the whole tub of Cool Whip.
Drizzle the fudge topping on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Ready to serve.

title: cinnamon crunchy toast
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix, oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine until crumbly.
Spread each slice of bread with additional soft margarine.
Sprinkle each slice of bread with crumbly mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 5 minutes.
Set oven control to broil.
Broil with tops about 3 inches from heat 2 minutes or until edges are brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: pear preserves cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, sifted flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg and buttermilk.
Mix.
Add nuts, preserves and vanilla.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: onion-broccoli bake
directions: Peel and cut onions into wedges.
Place in saucepan with water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in thawed broccoli.
Continue to simmer 3 to 5 minutes longer, until onions are just tender.
Drain vegetables well and place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat soup, milk and cream cheese over medium heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Pour over vegetables in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Toss crumbs in butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour oil and sugar over apples and let soak for 1 hour.
Beat eggs slightly; add to apple mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into bite sized flowerets. Combine vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients to make marinade.
Mix the marinade well and pour it over the vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: steak in a paper bag
directions: Mix oil, butter and Chachere's seasoning.
Spread on steak. Mix cheese and bread crumbs; spread on top.
Place on parchment sheet; put into brown bag and close.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°, then 10 minutes at 450°.

title: chicken with dried beef
directions: The amounts depend upon the number of chicken breasts to be used.

title: buttermilk pie crust dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add butter, shortening and buttermilk

title: oreo dessert
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.

title: buttermilk pan rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add buttermilk, oil and sugar. In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to yeast mixture and beat by hand until smooth. Do not knead. Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: waldorf crown salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water; chill until partially set.
Add apples, celery and walnuts.
Pour into lightly greased (with mayonnaise) ring mold; chill until set.
Mix the sour cream, marshmallows and salad dressing.
Unmold the salad and place salad dressing mixture in the center.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar.
Beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
(If using two 9-inch or three 8-inch layer pans, reduce time.)

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add milk, corn, seasonings and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Turn into a 1-quart buttered casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Tater Tots, and spread in pan. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas, one at a time, in oil for just a few seconds to soften in large skillet.
Dip each tortilla in a mixture of 2/3 cup enchilada sauce and 1/3 cup water which has been heated in another skillet; stack on a plate.

title: beef 'n potato bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine hash browns, oil and pepper.
Press into bottom and sides of dish to form a shell. Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in skillet, brown beef and drain; stir in gravy mix, water and garlic salt. Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables, reduce heat to medium and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions. Place in potato shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: holiday broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli with bouillon cubes and water until just tender. Heat soup to boiling.
Pour over broccoli.
Garnish with cheese and pimiento.
Serve at once.

title: sara's pimiento cheese(clinton, north carolina)
directions: Cut a red pepper into quarters.
Remove and discard seeds. Place in Pyrex dish with a little water.
Microwave uncovered at power 8 level until skin wrinkles and comes off easily.
Turn over occasionally.
Remove skin, chop into small pieces.
Grate the cheese and combine with the chopped pimiento, adding vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise until spreadable.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet; drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomato soup, catsup, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and oregano.
Cook on low heat 5 minutes.
Cook noodles; follow package directions.
Drain.

title: chocolate chip pudding
directions: Dip (approximately 4-5 seconds) enough cookies in milk to layer bottom of bowl.
Put layer of Cool Whip on top of cookies. Continue until bowl is full.
Layer top with Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, sunflower seeds, raisins, purple onion and bacon; toss with dressing.
You can make your own dressing with mayonnaise, wine vinegar and sugar to taste.
Real good.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Have cheese and butter at room temperature.
Mix and roll into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and press down with a fork. Bake at 350° about 8 minutes, until light brown.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Deseed and rinse peppers (recommend cutting tops off and then core).
Loosely stuff peppers with cheese.
Completely wrap each pepper with a thin layer of sausage. (Hint: The colder the sausage, the easier it is to work with.) Roll each pepper in finely crushed corn flakes.
Place on baking sheet and bake approximately 25 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Blend and spread over 2nd layer.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares to serve.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding (dry). Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Put in bowl and keep refrigerated.

title: holiday moments
directions: Beat butter with mixer in large bowl until light and fluffy. Add cornstarch and 1/3 cup powdered sugar; beat at low speed until moistened.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour; mix until dough forms.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate at least 1 hour for easier handling.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 9 to 15 minutes or until cookies are very light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
In small bowl, combine 3 tablespoons powdered sugar and both colors of decorator sugar and mix well.
Carefully roll warm cookies in sugars. Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: tomato quiche
directions: Combine tomatoes, butter, thyme and onion in saucepan and cook over medium heat until reduced by half (10 minutes).
Prepare pie crust(s).
Cover bottom with Swiss cheese and pour tomato mix on top.
Beat eggs well and add half and half or cottage cheese. Pour over tomato mixture.
Sprinkle on Italian seasoning or oregano.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° and 30 to 35 minutes at 375°. Cool 10 minutes before slicing.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat well.
Drain and discard fat. Add chopped onions and pepper.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Brown few minutes more.
Add chili powder and cumin.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk together.
Add unfrozen lemonade and stir.
Put in pie shell and place in refrigerator.

title: salmon balls
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 4 tablespoons liquid. Add baking powder to liquid. Beat in egg. Add onion and flaked salmon. Stir in enough flour to form mixture into balls the size of an egg. Fry in hot shortening until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: pate brisee
directions: Place metal blade in food processor.
Add ingredients, except water.
Process until coarse meal.
Add water with machine running until dough forms a ball.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Model or roll and cut dough. Bake until golden at 350°.
Cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat; add finely chopped onion.
Add the spices and peppers.
Add kidney beans and canned tomatoes.
Let simmer for approximately 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients. Add, one at a time, the next 5, making sure to beat well.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and sausage.
Add Bisquick gradually.
Form small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peach cream
directions: *Or substitute 1 (16 ounce) package frozen peaches.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Blend dry ingredients and add melted margarine or oil.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Add flavoring, if used.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet, leaving plenty of room to spread. Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 10 minutes.
Let stand a minute or so before removing from pan with spatula.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add Certo, and boil one minute more.
Remove from heat and let set 5 minutes; strain.
Add few drops food coloring.
Pour into hot sterilized jelly jars.
Yields 6 (8 ounce) jars.
Serve with cream cheese and crackers.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: *Put small amount in blender until all is powder.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted margarine and cracker crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream the cheese, softened margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Blend these ingredients well and smooth on top of graham cracker mixture.
Place bananas next, then pineapple. Spread whipped topping and sprinkle with a few chopped nuts.
Top with long stemmed cherries.
Chill well.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook rice until tender, according to package instructions. In large ovenproof dish, beat eggs. Whisk in vanilla, salt, sugar and milk. Add cooked rice. To prevent rice from sticking to sides, place dish in a larger ovenproof pan filled with 2-inches of water. Bake for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture over rice. Bake additional 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: corn dog muffins
directions: Mix cornbread mix and brown sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs and milk.
Add corn and hot dogs.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 14 to 18 minutes.
These are great for children's lunches.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter and
pepper until smooth.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Separate rolls and roll them out a little larger.
Fill with chicken filling and press dough together (like a diaper).
Roll rolls in melted butter, then in bread crumbs.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add vanilla and lemon juice; beat.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add sour cream and mashed bananas. Beat again.
Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder and mix well. Pour into greased bread tins.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken salad balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in this order: lettuce, onion, bell pepper, celery, frozen peas, mayonnaise, shredded cheese and then last, the bacon bits.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 15 minutes at 250°.

title: aunt lena's cookies
directions: Add sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in 3-quart pot. Bring to boil for exactly 4 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, oatmeal, nuts (optional) and vanilla.

title: pull-apart sweet loaf(star and news)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, butter and honey in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Reserve 1/2 tablespoon coconut for garnish.
Blend remaining coconut, cinnamon and nutmeg into glaze. Remove loaf from aluminum pan.
Make 4 vertical slices about 1 1/2 inches apart, stopping 1/2-inch above the bottom crust.
Open each slice and carefully spread 1 to 2 tablespoons of the glaze on one side of bread.
Press together.
Continue until all slices are filled.
Turn loaf one quarter.
Make another 4 cuts as described and fill with glaze.
Hold loaf together about 30 seconds and place back into aluminum pan.
Spread remaining glaze over top of bread. (If too thick, gently heat.)
Sprinkle with reserved coconut.
Bake 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 25 servings.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices and peel.
Parboil in a small amount of salted water until barely tender.
Remove and keep warm.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin, small pieces.
Cook in water until almost done.
Drain off most of the water, leaving enough to completely cook potatoes.
Add onion and celery.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook until onion and celery are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring almost to a boil.
Serve.

title: tuna bake
directions: In a saucepan, cook vegetables in butter until tender. Combine with soup, milk, macaroni, tomato and tuna in a 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, combine crackers, butter and cheese.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: orange glazed cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Salt and pepper the inside of each Cornish hen. You can truss the hens or close the opening with skewers but you don't have to do either.
Place the hens on a rack in a roasting pan.
Brush generously with melted butter or margarine.
Bake for about an 1 hour brushing with butter every 15 to 20 minutes. You might need to bake them a little longer if they don't seem to be done.
Heat the marmalade in a small saucepan. When the hens are done, remove from oven and brush with the marmalade. Return to the oven for about 2 to 3 minutes to glaze.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs one at a time.
Gradually add buttermilk.
Place pecans in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice in a bowl. Layer broccoli pieces and chicken cubes in baking dish.
Spread soup mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt butter in skillet and add bread crumbs.
Saute over medium heat until browned.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: raccoon in gravy
directions: Cut raccoon up into serving sizes.
Salt and pepper flour in a paper or plastic bag.
Add the meat and shake bag to coat with flour.
Fry in oil until browned.
Gradually add about a pint of water while stirring.
Add the garlic powder and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours or until tender.
Serve over rice or boiled potatoes.

title: christmas bread
directions: Scald milk and add sugar and salt.
When luke warm add dry yeast and 2 cups flour.
Beat well and let rise for 45 minutes. Mix eggs and shortening and add to yeast mixture.
Add remaining flour and fruit.
Knead and let rise.
Knead again and put into loaves and let rise again.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: pecan cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt until thick and creamy. Pour cheese mixture into uncooked, unpricked 9-inch pie crust. Sprinkle pecans over cheese mixture.
Beat eggs, Karo syrup, sugar and vanilla until blended and pour over cheese mixture and pecans.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add juice from lemons.
Stir in sugar.
Add water and cherries.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix everything together in a big bowl.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a large pan. Cover with water and bring to a boil.

Reduce heat and cook until potatoes can be pierced with knife (cooking time will depend on size of potatoes), usually about 30 minutes if potatoes are of average size. If uneven in size, it may be necessary to remove smaller potatoes as they are done. Drain in colander and cool in refrigerator.

title: bev's brunch beauty
directions: Saute potatoes and onions until partially cooked, then add roasted peppers.
Beat eggs in a bowl with milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add to sauteed mix and cover.
Cook over medium heat.
As frittata begins to puff, sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top, cover again and continue cooking until top is firm.
Serve immediately.

title: dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: verna's rhubarb cake
directions: Pour rhubarb in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar jello and flour.
Sprinkle over rhubarb, then sift cake mix over that. Then drop melted butter over top.
Pour water over that punching holes so the water will go down.
Try to get all the cake mix wet. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 325° until center bounces back when touched lightly.

title: speedy batter rolls
directions: Pour lukewarm water into mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in water. Stir well.
Add milk, shortening, egg and dry ingredients.
Mix on low speed of mixer until well blended.
Beat 2 minutes at moderate speed.
Cover with wax paper.
Set in warm place and let rise until dough is bulk.
Beat 20 to 30 stokes by hand.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin pans.
Cover and let rise until batter reaches top of pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown sausage. Drain. Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Do not roll.
Pat to right thickness and cut. Bake at 400° until done.

title: goulash
directions: Add macaroni and tomatoes.
Leave in skillet and cook slow.
If needed, add tomato juice or water to keep moist.
Cook 30 or 40 minutes.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in large bowl until well blended. Stir in Cool Whip; spread in crust and refrigerate.
Mix Jell-O pudding mix and water in medium saucepan until smooth, stirring constantly.
Cook on medium heat until mixture just comes to boil. Cool 5 minutes; stir in fruit.
Spoon over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: honey sour cream dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Stir well. Serve as a dip or dressing with fruit.

title: ginger crackles
directions: Measure
flour,
ginger,
baking
soda	and
salt
into sifter.
Cream shortening;	add sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses. Sift
dry
ingredients
over mixture;
blend well.	Make dough into balls	1-inch in diameter.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescents to rectangle shape.
Put on a cookie sheet and spread to fit pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch dressing together. Spread over cooled crescent thin.
Add your favorite chopped raw vegetables.
Cauliflower, broccoli and carrots are a good combination.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cut into squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour 3 times with cocoa.
Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs and food coloring.
Beat 10 minutes.
Add buttermilk, flour, salt and vanilla.
Remove from mixer.
Beat by hand, adding the vinegar and soda.
Put in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute onions in frying pan with oil; brown ground beef in same pan (season ground beef with salt and pepper to taste).
In casserole, mix all the ingredients except cheese.
(Be sure to drain cans of corn.)
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly.

title: igloos
directions: In medium bowl, cream butter and sugar; stir in pineapple well. In food processor, blender chop raisins and pecans until course. Stir into pineapple mixture and blend well.
Spread some of the mixture on three cookies.
Stack and gentle press together; top with a plain cookie.
Repeat for 10 stacks of 4 cookies each. Place stacks on a cookie sheet and let stand at room temperature at least 8 hours or overnight until cookies are very soft.
Beat cream, sugar and vanilla until stiff.
With narrow spatula, spread sides and tops of stacks with cream mixture.
Gently pat with coconut to coat.
Top with cherries (with stem).
Refrigerate up to 3 days.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown and drain meat, add remaining ingredients and stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on party rye.
Freeze until ready to serve, then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: mix jello and water let cool. Add 7-up when cold add pineapple, marshmallows and bananas. Let set till firm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a cake pan.
Mix peaches (drained but reserve juice) sugar and milk.
Pour into pan of melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; pour reserved peach juice over top and serve warm.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in water until tender.
Mix the flour, sugar and egg yolks.
Add raisins and mix well.

title: mexican corn soup
directions: In blender or food processor, blend corn and water until you have a smooth puree.
In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add corn puree and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and salt; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon color. Add condensed milk slowly. Combine lime juice with 3 tablespoons sugar and then add to mixture; mix well. In a separate bowl, add cream of tartar to egg whites and whip. When whites become foamy, begin adding sugar a little at a time until the whites peak. Fold 6 tablespoons of egg whites into the filling mixture. Pour filling into the pie shell. Top with the meringue. Bake at 330° until meringue turns golden brown. Let cool. Enjoy.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs in medium bowl. Add flour and sugars.
Mix well. Add butter and mix again. Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts. Carefully spoon into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix in blender avocados, cream cheese, Beau Monde and Lawry salt.
Spread on large platter about 1/2-inch thick.
Top with remaining ingredients and serve with Tostitos chips.

title: tangy pork cutlets
directions: Place crushed cereal in shallow dish or pan; set aside.
In a second dish or pan, beat egg and lemon juice until foamy.
In a third shallow dish or pan, stir together flour, salt and pepper. Dip cutlets in flour mixture, then dip in egg mixture.
Coat with crushed cereal.

title: cheese 'n chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in large skillet until tender.
Stir in chicken, picante sauce, cream cheese, green chillies and cumin; cook until thoroughly heated. Stir in 1 cup cheese.
Spoon chicken mixture into tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down in a 12 x 7-inch baking dish; top with enchilada sauce and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk jello salad(sugar free)
directions: Bring sugar, Jell-O, pineapple and juice to a boil.
Let cool. Mix buttermilk and Cool Whip together.
Then mix all together well. Refrigerate in 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Prepare jello with boiling water.
Drain juice from pineapple and add 1 cup to jello.
Add softened cream cheese, pecans, pineapple and whipped Dream Whip; set until firm in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Brown slowly on both sides in skillet in a little oil.
Drain chops and put in a casserole dish.
Pour soup, milk and water over chops.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Goes great served over rice!

title: beef dumpling stew
directions: Thoroughly brown meat on all sides in hot fat.
Add water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, medium sliced onion, bay leaves and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally, to keep from sticking.
Add vegetables and continue cooking 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
(If potatoes are added, they do not take as long to cook as the carrots and onion.)
Now add dumplings.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the egg, sugars and shortening.
Add milk and dry ingredients.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients; spoon into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with sliced green onions, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: low-fat salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties, size 3 to 4-inches. Place on broiling rack and bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Turn over and bake 10 minutes more.

title: fried eggplant supreme
directions: Peel and slice eggplant 1/2-inch thick and place in bowl. Sprinkle with salt and add enough water to cover eggplant completely.
Soak 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Beat the pancake mix together with the milk.
Combine cracker meal and seasoning. Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Dip eggplant slices in pancake batter, then in cracker meal mixture.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until slightly thickened.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 400° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: to clean silverware
directions: Fill gallon aluminum kettle 3/4 full of water.
Add 3 tablespoons of Ivory soap flakes.
Bring to a boil.
Add silverware.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove.
Rinse with hot water.
Rub thoroughly with a soft, dry towel.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine corn flakes and nuts in small bowl.
Mix cream cheese, chives, 2 tablespoons butter and salt.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Spread about 1/4 cup chicken mixture on each roll and roll up, starting at short end.
(Rolling pin helps to enlarge crescent roll.)
Tuck sides under to seal.
Roll in melted butter and then nut mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with chicken gravy.

title: holiday squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs (one at a time).
Add flour and vanilla.
Spread in pan (10 x 15-inch), greased and floured.
Lightly score (with toothpick) dough to make 24 squares. Put 1 teaspoon Comstock pie filling in center of each square. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still warm.
Cool and cut into 24 squares.

title: tortilla stack
directions: Layer 1 shell, then ingredients in order given.
Dab butter around edges so it won't burn, then repeat layers until 4 to 5 high ending with tortilla on top.
Bake at 350° covered in foil for 20 minutes until cheese is melted.
Open foil for a few minutes to get top done.
Cool before cutting.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in large skillet.
Simmer on top of stove for one hour or until tender.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Blend margarine with cream cheese. Add 1 cup flour; mix thoroughly. Shape into small balls. Press into small muffin cups. Beat egg. Add 1 tablespoon flour and remaining ingredients. Pour into pastry shells; fill 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until filling is almost set. Reduce oven temperature to 250°. Bake for 10 minutes longer or until filling is firm. Cool in muffin cups.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except beef.
Mix well.
Add beef; mix well.
Press into a loaf; bake 1 hour. Drain; let stand 5 minutes.

title: mince pie
directions: Saute tomatoes and apples in butter in a large, heavy skillet or frying pan for five minutes over medium heat.
Add sugar, molasses and spices.
Stir well while simmering for five minutes. Add raisins, pecans, vanilla and lemon peel.
Simmer, uncovered, until most of the liquid has evaporated.

title: easy chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a mixing bowl, beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until soft and creamy.
Add whipped topping, folding until smooth.
Spread over crumb crust and sprinkle with pecans.
May serve immediately or store in refrigerator.

title: spinach salad
directions: Blend first six ingredients and chill.
Mix remaining ingredients, add dressing and toss.

title: special jello surprise
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package, omitting 1/2 cup cold water.
After dissolving Jell-O, add fruit and 1/2 cup juice and yogurt.
Stir until blended.
Add whipped topping.
Beat with rotary beater until frothy.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stir several times to keep mixed, until set.
Coordinate Jell-O flavor and yogurt flavor.

title: bacon and swiss dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese on medium for 30 seconds.
Mix cream cheese and salad dressing, Swiss cheese and onions until well blended.
Spoon into a 2 1/2 cups casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes or until well heated, turning every 2 minutes and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream butter, oil and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until tested done.

title: cabbage-coconut-pineapple salad
directions: Mix cabbage, coconut, pineapple and mayonnaise. Add salt. Toss lightly. Nuts may be added, if desired.
Add pineapple juice if mixture is dry. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Do not mix more than 2 minutes. Pour batter into Bundt pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and 10 minutes on rack to allow chips to melt. Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: andy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well and bring to a boil.
Baste meat while cooking.

title: spinach pom poms
directions: Thaw spinach.
Drain and squeeze out all excess moisture.
Mix together all ingredients.
Shape into balls, the size of walnuts. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Press with tines of fork to flatten. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 350° preheated oven for 8 minutes or until light brown around the edges.

title: broccoli rice casserole iii
directions: Cook rice; set aside. Cook broccoli and drain; set aside. Saute celery in butter until tender. Combine soup, milk and cheese. Stir in rice, broccoli and celery. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit; place in long glass dish. Pour 8 ounces bourbon over fruit and stir until mixed. Cover with plastic wrap. Let set overnight.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Slip out of pan immediately and cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: potato bake
directions: Let hash browns set until thawed. Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sausage upside-down casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage, onion and pepper until sausage is brown and crumbly.
Stir in flour.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese and olives.
Spread evenly in square pan.
Prepare muffin mix; spread over sausage.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes; loosen edge.
Invert onto plate.
Serves 6.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all together. Drop from teaspoon 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet, pressing down ends of coconut with back of spoon. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: sara's squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, cheese and onions.
Beat eggs; add milk. Season with salt and pepper.
Add to the 1st three ingredients. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add bread crumbs, dotted with butter, as topping.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together cornmeal, soda, salt, salad oil, milk and eggs. Add creamed corn.
Pepper can be added to meat if desired.
Spray Pam in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into pan, then sprinkle the ground beef, peppers and cheese over the mixture. Pour remaining half of mixture over this.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Serve with beans and salad. We like taco sauce over the cornbread too.

title: chunk sweet pickles (good!)
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into 3/4-inch chunks.
Place in a stone jar and pour over them the pickling salt dissolved in 1 gallon of boiling water.
Let stand 1 week, stirring each day.
On the 8th day, drain well and pour 1 gallon of fresh water over them.
On the 9th day, drain and add 1 gallon of fresh boiling water with alum dissolved in it over them.
On the 10th day, drain and pour on 1 gallon of fresh boiling water.
On the 11th day, drain and put in a clean stone jar.
Combine vinegar, 6 cups sugar, cinnamon and cloves and pour over boiling hot.
On the 12th, 13th and 14th day, drain, reheat liquid and add 1 cup of sugar each day.
On the 15th day, heat liquid and pack pickles in jars.
Pour hot liquid over them and seal.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut orange slices and dates in small pieces.
Chop nuts and coat all with flour.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add coconut, nuts, candy and dates.
Mix thoroughly with hands or wooden spoon. Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and pour a syrup of 1 cup fresh orange juice and 2 cups of powdered sugar over hot cake.
Let stand until completely cold before removing from pan.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix and chill until ready to serve.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Using large bowl, combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Mix at high speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cook your rhubarb covered with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes. Drain, then stir in butter. Separate your eggs.
Beat yolks, then blend in sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Gradually stir in your milk. Spread rhubarb in prepared 9-inch pie plate. Pour milk mixture over it. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.

title: saucepan fudgies
directions: In large heavy saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat,
stirring
constantly.
Remove
from
heat.
Cool slightly. Beat
in
sugar.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly. Stir
in
vanilla.
Mix
flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Chill about 30 minutes. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and bake on ungreased sheet for 18 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes with salt until firm (use just enough water to boil).
Take out potatoes.
Keep water and add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly until cheeses are melted.
Add potatoes and serve.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and chives.
Add milk if too thick.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Roll tablespoon of mix into a ball.
Press down crisscross with a fork on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: carol's rolls, bread and scones(easy dough for rolls, bread and scones)
directions: Take 1/2 cup of warm water and mix in yeast; set aside. Dissolve sugar
and
salt
in
remaining
water.
Add
oil and yeast.
Stir
in
flour
and
knead dough on a lightly floured surface.
Cover dough and let rise in a warm place (80°) until double.
Makes 2 loaves of bread or 12 large rolls and lots of scones.
Fry scones in hot oil at 375°.

title: mayo parmesan bread
directions: Stir together cheese and mayo.
If desired, stir in chives. Broil 1 side of 4 to 5 slices French bread 1 minute or until toasted.
Spread some of mixture on toasted side and broil 2 to 3 minutes.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: Saute onion and garlic until tender in melted butter.
Add oregano, parsley, cheese and shrimp; heat until hot, but not boiling.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: italian pasta bake(makes 6 servings)
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain. Stir in pasta, sauce and 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese. Spoon into 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese and remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes on medium speed. Pour into 3 cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Punch holes in cool cake with a toothpick.

title: oatmeal-coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until top and crust are golden brown.

title: 7-up banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs, beating after each one.
Add vanilla and bananas.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with 7-Up.
Add in nuts; pour into bread baking pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: sole francais
directions: Heat oil on medium high in frying pan.
Coat each fillet with flour on both sides.
Dip fillet in egg and then place in the heated oil.
Lightly brown each side of fillet.
Remove fillet to a baking dish or small sheet pan.
On medium heat, combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Pour liquid over fish. Place in 350° oven, preheated, for 8 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine orange Jell-O and boiling water in saucepan; stir until Jell-O dissolved.
Place pan over flame and add cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Place pan in cold water until cool. Add fruit cocktail and 2 cups ice water.
Let set in refrigerator until slightly set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in mold.
Ready in about 3 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and gradually add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each.
Add flavorings.
Add flour.
Add sour cream.
Don't beat too much after adding sour cream.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.
Warning:
Do not open oven door!

title: white coconut cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add shortening, water and milk.
Mix well.
Add egg whites and beat 2 minutes. Fold in coconut and vanilla.
Bake at 325°.

title: pampy's cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set awhile to blend flavors (overnight is best).
A family tradition for shrimp and oysters.

title: white chip orange cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter and both sugars in large bowl until creamy.
Beat egg and orange peel. Gradually beat in flour mixture; stir in morsels.
Drop dough by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: warming shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat broiler.
Prepare 4 servings of mashed potatoes according to package directions using milk, butter and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.
Cook ground beef in medium broiler proof skillet over medium-high heat, stirring to separate meat until browned and crumbly.
Drain skillet drippings.
Sprinkle ground beef with remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and the black pepper. Add beef gravy and mixed vegetables to meat; stir well.
Cook meat mixture over medium-low heat until hot, about 5 minutes. Spoon the mashed potatoes in a ring around outside edge of skillet leaving 3-inch circle in center.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan evenly over mashed potatoes.
Broil 4 to 5-inches from heat until Parmesan is golden, about 3 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper and celery, then drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, catsup, salt and pepper.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans and simmer for another 15 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil rapidly brown sugar, corn syrup, butter, salt and cream of tartar for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add baking soda and mix thoroughly.
Pour over fresh corn. Mix well and pour on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour in a 200° oven.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: home-style oat patties
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Combine all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto a nonstick cookie sheet lightly coated with vegetable shortening.
Brown in a 350° oven until cooked through, 15 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle pieces of meat with meat tenderizer according to label instructions.
Mix flour and pepper in a small bowl and coat meat thoroughly.
Heat oil in Dutch oven over moderate heat.
Add meat and brown well on both sides.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms and simmer (covered) over low heat or bake in the oven (about 250°) for about 2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pixies (cookies)
directions: Combine melted margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients (except for powdered sugar).
Chill overnight.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Roll dough into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl until it looks like whipped butter.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Cream butter, white sugar and brown sugar. Add vanilla and eggs.
Stir well.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Add oatmeal and nuts to other ingredients.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop with teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes.
Take up right away.

title: pretty no-guilt sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer until light.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour.
Tear 3 sheets of wax paper about 12 inches long.
Form dough into rolls on paper (approximately 1 1/2 inches in diameter).
Dough will be very soft.
Roll dough in a thick layer of colored sugar.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until firm.
May be stored in refrigerator several days or frozen for several weeks.
Preheat oven to 375°. Remove from paper and slice thin with a very sharp knife.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: corn flake pudding
directions: Combine flour and sugar with milk; add eggs, slightly beaten, then add margarine.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add vanilla and corn flakes.

title: spaghetti sauce(in crock-pot)
directions: Brown hamburg.
Drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Add all rest of ingredients and cook on low setting for the day.
Enjoy!!

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate, marshmallows and milk, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Chill 1 hour or until completely cooled.
Fold in whipped cream. Turn into pastry shell.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
If desired, garnish with additional whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: holiday carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes or until carrots are just about tender, stirring once. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly to coat evenly. Makes about 10 servings, 65 calories each.

title: scotch ice cream pie
directions: Combine milk and ice cream in mixing bowl.
Blend until smooth.
Add pudding mix and beat slowly with egg beater, just until well mixed.
Stir
in
nuts.	Pour
immediately into pie shell.
Chill until set.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts.

title: uncle michael's noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles, then rinse and drain. Mix the remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the noodles and gently stir. Place in 8 x 10 dish, lightly greased. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until lightly browned.

title: kids quesadillas
directions: Place one tortilla on plate, sprinkle cheese on top. Place other tortilla on cheese. Microwave for 45 seconds. Remove from microwave. Hot! Let cool for one minute. Cut into quarters, eat. You can add chips, dip, etc. Enjoy!!!

title: walking salad
directions: Core the apple.
Fill with peanut butter, nuts and raisins. Wrap in foil or plastic bag and carry along on a hike.

title: eva's chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken in enough water to have 1 1/2 quarts broth.
Chop and saute peppers and onions in oleo.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth.
Add tomatoes (mash and use 1/2 juice) and Worcestershire. Cook until thickened; add peas.
Chop mushrooms (drained), onions and peppers.
Add shredded cheese and stir until melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped chicken last.
Put in casserole. May freeze now and cook later or
bake for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; mix together and refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Whip whipping cream until thickened.
Fold into Jell-O mixture.
Cut a baked angel food cake in layers.
Put each layer back in pan with strawberry mixture between layers; refrigerate overnight.
Remove from pan and frost with whipping cream before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugars, Crisco, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: david's dad's salad dressing
directions: Put all but Blue cheese in blender and blend until smooth. Pour into glass storage container.
Stir in blue cheese (crumbled).
Cover tightly; chill several hours.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: frozen fruit pop(fun food for kids to make themselves)
directions: Will also need 12 (3 ounce) paper cups and 12 wooden sticks.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings(messy but good!)
directions: Break wings into thirds and discard tips.
Combine beaten egg and water; set aside.
Combine 1/2 teaspoon salt, flour and cornstarch in a large Ziploc bag.
Dip each piece of wing into egg/water mixture, then into Ziploc bag with flour mixture; coat evenly.
Brown in hot oil and let drain on paper towel.
Place browned chicken into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, vinegar, broth, catsup and soy sauce in a saucepan. Bring to a simmer.
Pour over chicken wings.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, basting every 20 minutes.
Sauce will thicken during the final 15 minutes.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground chuck
and
onion in shortening; add mushrooms, tomato soup
and
season (salt, pepper, etc.) to taste. Simmer 1 to 2
hours;
last	half
hour add sour cream.
Serve stroganoff over cooked egg noodles or rice.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl and add dressing.

title: banana strawberry slush
directions: In blender, mix together all ingredients until smooth and ice is finely crushed.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger with the taco seasoning.
Layer the next 4 ingredients in order given in a large bowl..
Add the cooled hamburger and Cheddar cheese.
Chill.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Put layer of lettuce, layer of cauliflower and a few onions; sprinkle with cheese.
Continue this until lettuce and cauliflower are gone.
Put dressing on top.
(Do not toss.)
Cover tight and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and margarine with pastry blender, save 1 cup for topping.
To the remaining mixture add egg, vanilla, baking soda and buttermilk.
Stir lightly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle on topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey dressing - for fruit salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion.
Pour oil into mixture very slowly, beating constantly with rotary beater.
Makes 2 cups.

title: no bake cookies(from the files of charlie mae williams)
directions: Mix sugar, butter or margarine, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute only.
Add vanilla and stir in 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups uncooked oatmeal.
Quickly drop them on waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator when cool.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: turkey loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients in order listed above; mix well. Press evenly into 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Drain off any excess fat. Let stand for 10 minutes and transfer to serving platter. Serves 4-6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook in double boiler until mixture boils.
Place vanilla wafers or gingernaps around dish alternating with bananas and cover with sauce.
Makes 2 nice layers.
Top with wafers.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend
the
Crisco and sugar.
Add
well
beaten
eggs. Mash bananas and add with vanilla.
Sift
dry
ingredients and add to banana mixture.
This bread contains no
milk or water. Makes 1 large or 2 small loaf pans.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together pink lemonade and lemon juice.
Add Eagle Brand milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts. Chill until set.

title: banana-chocolate chip bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure dry ingredients and chips.
Mix together in a large bowl and set aside.
Use food processor or blender to mix shortening, sugar, juice, eggs and bananas and process until smooth.

Pour banana mixture into bowl with dry ingredients and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour batter into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake for about 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack before slicing.
Tastes great plain or with cream cheese.
The perfect recipe for very ripe bananas!

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put all ingredients in a large skillet.
Cover.
Bring to boil and cook for 1 minute.
Uncover.
Lower heat and turn with spatula until barely tender (about 5 minutes).
Toss with more Parmesan. Serves 6 to 8.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Peel, boil and cube potatoes; drain.
Combine with celery and onion.
Combine salad dressing mix, mayonnaise and water.
Add to potato mixture.
Toss to coat.
Chill and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: appetizer-sausage roll
directions: Fry and crumble sausage; drain well.
Add cream cheese to sausage; melt and stir in well.
Open 1 package rolls.
Take half of dough and press seams together.
Put half of sausage mixture on dough and top with other half of dough, which you have pressed the seams together on.
Repeat with other package of rolls.
Makes 2 rolls.
Sprinkle rolls with seed, if desired.
Bake at 350° until rolls are browned.
Slice and serve.

title: quick chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken in white wine and diced garlic clove.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Place chicken in pan.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Pour remaining sauce over baked potato or wild rice.
M-m-m good!

title: greek pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, cook the onions and garlic with salt in 2 Tbsp. olive oil, until the onions are clear and soft.
Add herbs, lemon juice and spinach and cook over fairly high heat, stirring, until the spinach is limp and the liquid is evaporated.
tags: lots of freshly ground black pepper

title: french bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into 1/2 cup warm water.
In large bowl, dissolve sugar and salt in remaining water.
Add shortening and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and mix well again.
Set in warm place and work through dough with spoon at 10-minute intervals, 5 times.
Divide dough and turn half onto lightly floured board.
Shape into rectangle and roll firmly as for jelly roll.
Seal edge.
Repeat for other half.
Place rolls, sealed side down, on greased baking sheet.
Score tops diagonally 6 times. Cover with towel and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and brush with melted butter.
(Good hard crust with 4 1/2 cups flour.)

title: fruit medley(diabetic)
directions: Combine pineapple, orange slices, apple and cherries in a medium bowl.
Gently fold in yogurt.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Yield:
7 servings.
Each serving amount:
1 cup.
Exchanges:
1 fruit and 1 fat.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a Dutch oven and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, dried beef and dressing by hand. Make into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: easy penuche icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until thick enough to spread.
If icing gets stiff, add a little hot water.

title: tuna schooner
directions: Mix and spread on buttered French toast.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat banana split dessert
directions: Mix cheesecake mix with skimmed milk and lite margarine in graham cracker crust.
Make in large oblong pan.
Top with layers of bananas and strawberries (sliced in small pieces).
Top with can of crushed pineapple.
Ice with softened topping and garnish with pecans and cherries.
Serve with chocolate syrup.

title: peach crinkle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread drained peaches in a 10-inch baking dish. Crumble together pie crust and brown sugar and sprinkle over peaches.
Top with pats of butter and lemon rind. Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let set for 15 to 20 minutes and serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add
ground beef and rice.
Spread 3 cups of cabbage in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Spread with remaining 3 cups cabbage.
Add tomato soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: quick easy fruit crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cake mix and drizzle with melted butter.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cinnamon-apple jell
directions: Put candies into 1 cup hot water in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until the candies melt. Add Jell-O to the hot liquid and stir until it dissolves. Add applesauce and pour into a quart mold.
Chill until firm. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Brown meat in olive
oil
in the bottom of a big pot or frying pan,
if	using
a
crock-pot.
Dump
all
the
other ingredients in and simmer
for
hours or so.
I just put it all in a stockpot
and	cook it overnight, covered, at 250° in the oven.
You have to	cook
it a long time so the meat falls off the bones, otherwise it's frustrating.

title: mixed bean salad with dressing
directions: Drain beans and rinse in cold water.
Mix together.

title: cheerios treat
directions: Heat brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in pan.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until bubbly around edges. Cook uncovered 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda until foamy and light colored.
Pour over cereal, peanuts and raisins in greased bowl.
Spread evenly in greased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 15 minutes; stir and let stand just until cool, 10 minutes.
Loosen mixture with metal spatula.
Let stand until firm, about 30 minutes.
Break into bite size pieces.
Makes approximately 10 cups.

title: frozen strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping; blend well.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into crust and freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with additional whole strawberries.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown hamburger; pour off grease.
Add diced fresh mushrooms.
Cook for a few minutes, then take off stove.
Spoon 1 cup sauce into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside remaining sauce.

title: oxtails romana
directions: Brown oxtails in 1 tablespoon oil (they will make more as they brown), using ovenproof Dutch oven or other large pot that has a cover.
Turn oxtails with tongs until nicely browned on all sides.

title: vanilla drop cookies
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking soda and salt and sift together 3 times. Work butter with spoon until creamy. Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition until light and fluffy. Add eggs and blend well. Add flour alternately with milk, beating after each addition until smooth. Add vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until brown. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: ruth martin's m-f-a pickles
directions: Cover pickles and seal cold.

title: cream pie
directions: Fill pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Put in hot oven (375°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir several times until it thickens.

title: venison or deer steaks
directions: Slice fresh meat and let soak in dressing for 4 to 5 hours. Drain and rub with mustard.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper; fry in oil until golden brown.

title: sauteed spinach and green onion
directions: Melt butter in large skillet and add onion.
Saute onion until tender.
Add spinach which has add stems removed.
Cover and cook until tender over medium heat, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Cook 2 cups blueberries, sugar, cornstarch, salt, and water until thick and clear.
Then add butter or margarine and lemon juice.
Let cool.
Then stir in remaining 2 cups of blueberries and put in cooked graham cracker crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cheerio clusters
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients over low heat until smooth. Add Cheerios and peanuts.
Stir and drop by spoonfuls on buttered wax paper. Chill.

title: salmon ball
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Let cream cheese soften. Mix thoroughly salmon and cream cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke and horseradish (these amounts can be changed according to taste).
Form into a ball, roll in nuts and refrigerate.
This can be used as a dip without the nuts.
Makes a nice hors d'oeuvres, or dip for cocktail parties.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.
Taste and adjust seasonings. Delicious with snow peas or broccoli.

title: chocolate-peanut butter pie
directions: Generously butter a 10-inch pie pan; set aside.
Prepare brownies as directed on package, spread in prepared pan, and bake at 350° about 20 minutes, until edges are set and middle is somewhat liquid.
With back of a greased spoon, move batter away from middle and up sides so that a rim is formed and the shape is that of a pie shell.
Return to oven and continue baking at 350° 10-15 minutes longer, until center is set.
Remove from oven and press peanuts into bottom and up sides of shell.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast in 1/2 cup of above warm water.
Mix dry ingredients. Add eggs, oil, remaining water and yeast; mix well.
Let rise till double, punch down, make into rolls, pinch off, place in pan with oil or butter, roll in oil then butter.
Let rise again then bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: bird of a feather pancakes
directions: Blend all ingredients on medium high speed for 2 minutes. Pour batter into a greased and hot skillet.
Cook until golden brown, alternating both sides.
Makes 12 (4-inch radius) pancakes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine eggs, milk and seasoning. Stir in potatoes, cheese, onion, green pepper and ham. Pour in 9 x 13 pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean. Spray pan with Pam.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; drain spaghetti.
Mix spaghetti and cheese until cheese is melted. Add tomatoes, onion, pepper, soup, corn and pimento; mix well. Pour into casserole dish; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pink congealed salad
directions: Make Jell-O; let thicken a little, then whip.
Add mayonnaise and cream cheese; mix thoroughly.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, pecans and Dream Whip that has been made according to directions on box.
Mix well; chill until firm.

title: caramel crunch apple pie
directions: Combine caramels and water in a microwave safe bowl.
Heat in microwave until caramels melt, stirring occasionally.
Arrange half of the apple slices in the pie shell.
Drizzle with half of the melted caramels.
Add the remaining apple slices and drizzle with the remaining caramels.
Combine flour, sugar, and cinnamon.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in walnuts or pecans.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: easy fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with wax paper.
Stir chocolate chips and sweetened condensed milk over low heat until melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pan and refrigerate.

title: granny ernie's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and oil well.
Add eggs and vanilla, then dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll size of walnuts, flatten lightly.
Top each with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, 1/3 of a large white onion and cilantro into a chopper/grinder (I use the AS SEEN ON TV kind).
Add a squirt of lemon juice and a squirt of lime juice and a pinch of salt.
Add jalapeno peppers as desired.

title: creamy sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes.
Mix in sugar, eggs, milk, butter and nutmeg and mix until creamy and smooth.
Pour in crust and bake at 250°.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion, celery and cucumber fine.
Mix gelatin and cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight; spread on crackers or bread.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease and add rest of ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 20-30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry cream pie
directions: Crush cookies in blender; add margarine and blend well.
Press into pie plate.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop onions and peppers (after removing seeds) fine; add remaining ingredients and stew all together for 1 1/2 hours. Remove spices and can.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons of the sugar.
Put this in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.
Let this cool.
Mix together cream cheese, the remaining sugar until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Prepare the Jell-Os with the boiling water.
Mix in the frozen strawberries.
Set in refrigerator until almost firm.
Pour cream cheese mixture over the pretzel crust as soon as the crust cools. When the strawberry mixture is ready, add it to the pan. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: rakott prumple (layer potatoes)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water; pare and slice.
Arrange 1/3 of slices in greased baking dish.
Over this, slice 3 eggs and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with half of sour cream.
Make another layer and a final layer of potatoes.
Top with the crumbs, mixed with melted butter and a bit of paprika.
Add the heavy cream. Bake in a hot oven (400° to 450°) for 30 minutes or until crumbs brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: venison party spread
directions: Blend thoroughly; chill. Serve on party crackers. This also makes an excellent sandwich spread. An excellent way to make use of leftover venison roast.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Combine oil and next 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Place cereal in bowl. Brush each piece chicken with mixture, then dip in cereal crumbs until evenly coated.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes until chicken is golden brown and tender.
Timing may vary according to thickness of chicken.

title: sugar drop or filled cookies
directions: Drop and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes creole
directions: Cut boiled sweet potatoes lengthwise; place in shallow pan. Cover generously with butter and brown sugar.
Add mace, salt and orange rind.
Bake at 375° until sugar and butter have formed a thick syrup, about 1 hour.
Very good with baked ham or ham croquettes.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in Dutch oven until brown; drain. Add onions, cabbage and celery; cook and stir until vegetables are light brown.
Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans (with liquid), water, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Shred cheese and let stand at room temperature overnight or several hours.
Mix with sausage and Bisquick until smooth.
Make into small round balls.
Place in covered containers and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cranberry apple chutney(great at thanksgiving and christmas)
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a large heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes. Add the fruit.
Return to boil.
Turn heat to low and cook until mixture starts to thicken, approximately 1 hour, stirring often (the chutney will thicken as it cools).
Remove from heat and divide into containers.
Store in refrigerator or freezer. Goes great with almost anything.

title: italian chili
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add all ingredients and cook at a high boil for 20 minutes, then simmer for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: make-ahead fruit salad
directions: Fold together in serving bowl.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: great salad
directions: Combine lettuce, cauliflower, cooked bacon and thinly sliced onion in salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese into smooth dressing.
Pour over salad and top with grated cheese. Chill and serve.
May be made 1 hour ahead of serving.

title: currant wieners
directions: Mix jelly and mustard together in medium pan.
Heat until dissolved into syrup.
Add wieners.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Fry bacon; dry and crumble.
Mix with broccoli, raisins and onions.

title: copper sticks
directions: Slice and boil carrots in saltwater until fork tender. Drain and cool. Mix with other vegetables and cover with marinade.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Combine meat, Veg-All and cream of mushroom soup in casserole bowl.
Cut up Velveeta cheese and mix with spoon.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat the oven and baking sheet to 425°.
Boil the potatoes until almost done. Add the broccoli flowerets the last 1 to 2 minutes of cooking time or add the mixed vegetables the last 2 minutes.

In a large saucepan, combine butter, flour and pepper. Cook over medium-low heat until mixture is bubbly and thick. Gradually stir in broth and milk and stir until mixture begins to thicken. Add cheese and stir until melted. Fold in chicken and potatoes-broccoli mixture.
Pour into pie crust. Moisten edges with water. Top with other crust. Crimp edges. Slit top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: milk duds cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with sugar until light and thick. Beat whites until stiff; fold into yolk mixture.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, onion and carrots until soft with fork (not mushy).
Melt oleo and add dressing mix.
In another container, mix sour cream and soup.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
First, put dressing mix.
Next, put squash and carrots, 1/2 sour cream and soup, then crumbs, squash and sour cream.
Top with crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: junk yard salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
May also be frozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of large baking dish.
Slice potatoes to cover.
Slice onion and cover potatoes.
Pour soup over top.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover; bake 40 more minutes.

title: festive cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix and sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in almonds.
Beat eggs; mix oil, almond extract, bananas and undrained pineapple.
Add to dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Spoon into well-oiled tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, milk and cocoa on low heat. Bring slowly to a boil and boil for 3 minutes; beat in oleo.
Serve over chocolate cake and ice cream for a hot fudge cake.

title: portuguese vegetable soup
