directions: In large pot, combine water, beef shank, split peas, salt and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Reduce; simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Remove beef shank.
Cool shank, then remove meat and dice it, then return to pot.
Add sausage, tomatoes, carrots, onion and green pepper.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Add macaroni and simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Put the saltine crumbs in a bowl.
Pour the melted butter over them; toss lightly.
Butter an 8-inch cake pan; spread a third of the crumb mixture on the bottom.
Drain the oysters, saving the liquid.
Cover crumbs with 1/2 the oysters; sprinkle with pepper and the second third of the crumbs, then the rest of the oysters and more pepper.
Combine the oyster liquid with milk or cream to make 1 cup.
Stir in the Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over the oysters; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 4.
Good for a side dish for Thanksgiving or Christmas dinner.

title: pineapple fruit dip
directions: Heat juice.
Add beaten egg.
Whisk with an eggbeater.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Cool.
Serve with fruit chunks.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all these ingredients and pour into casserole dish.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and gently mix together.
Serve immediately or chill first.
Yield:
5 cups.

title: imperial butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk and mix.
Stir in zucchini.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add and mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Drop by teaspoonful into deep grease for 10 minutes.

title: quick pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Chill.

title: lemon refrigerator cheesecake
directions: Thoroughly mix 3/4 cup sugar, gelatin and salt.
Stir in egg yolks and evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add peel; cool.
Stir in cottage cheese, lemon juice and vanilla.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds when spooned.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: no bake date cookies
directions: Blend together sugar, dates, butter, egg and vanilla; cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add walnuts.
Cool slightly and add Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: pappy's sweet pickles
directions: Fill gallon jar with washed whole cucumbers.
Add salt, alum and pickling spices.
Now pour vinegar (5%) over cucumbers. Finish filling jar with water.
Put lid on tight and shake jar until all is dissolved.
Date jar and let stand for 2 or 3 weeks. Drain all liquid from pickles, saving pickling spices, to add back to pickles.
Chunk or slice pickles, then add sugar over the pickles and shake jar until all sugar turns to liquid.
Let stand 2 or 3 days, then "eat them up".
You do not have to keep them in the refrigerator.

title: bertha's cookie sheet cake
directions: Cover raisins and dates with water.
Bring to a boil.
Makes about 1 cup juice.
Add shortening and sugar while warm.
Then add flour, salt, nutmeg, soda, egg and nuts.
Spread on rimmed cookie sheet and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
You may add mixed candied fruit to dates and raisins, if desired.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients except the flour.
Mix well.
Take a little piece of the mix, roll into a ball, put in pan.
Put two fingers in flour.
Push down on ball with fingers.
Do rest the same.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Yields 10 to 20 cookies.

title: steamboat omelet
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch deep pan for 8 portions.
Place 8 slices of bread in pan.
Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese on bread.
Top with 8 slices of bread which has the top buttered. Beat eggs, add spices, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Pour over bread; you may refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, melt butter and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Wash, drain well and chop spinach.
Chop egg whites (reserve yolks).
Combine all ingredients, except egg yolks.
Toss together lightly.
Just before serving, sieve egg yolks and garnish top of salad.

title: mexican pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Saute onion and green pepper until tender. Stir in beans, salsa, red bell pepper, olives, corn, chili powder, cayenne and black pepper. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes. Spoon half of the mixture into one of the pie crusts and cover with half of the cheese. Repeat with remaining beans and cheese. Top with remaining crust. Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil together for 6 minutes the sugar, salt, butter and milk. Put the chocolate pieces, sweet chocolate, Marshmallow Creme and nuts in a large bowl.
Pour the boiling mixture over and beat until the chocolate is melted.
Pour into greased pan; let cool. Let stand several hours before cutting.
Makes about 5 pounds of fudge.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into two pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes until golden brown and firm.

title: summertime meat loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, lightly beat together eggs.
Add 1 cup tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix. To mixture, add bread crumbs, milk, beef and onion.
Mix lightly. Shape into 6 oval loaves.
Cook in butter in large skillet over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine remaining tomato sauce to 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Turn meat loaves and brush with sauce.
Cook 5 minutes more or until done.
Heat remaining sauce and spoon over meat.
Yields 6 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
Add 2 tsp. to 1 cup water.

title: quick corn soup
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces in soup pot.
Add onion and cook until done.
Now add potatoes, corn and water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add butter, milk and seasoning.
Reheat to boiling. Serves 5.

title: easy clam dip
directions: Mix together and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy skillet. Add chicken and brown on all sides. Remove from skillet. Add onions and garlic to oil remaining in skillet and cook until onions are tender, but not brown, stirring occasionally. Return chicken to skillet and add the tomatoes, green peppers and bay leaf.
Mix salt, pepper, celery seed and oregano; blend with tomato sauce.
Pour over all. Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Blend in wine and cook, uncovered, for about 20 minutes longer. Discard bay leaf. Put the cooked spaghetti onto a hot serving platter and top with the chicken and sauce.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: layered potato-beef casserole
directions: Mix raw hamburger with onions, salt and pepper.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and cover with the condensed soup. Sprinkle the grated cheese on top of soup and arrange sliced potatoes on top of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel pie
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar in skillet over medium heat. Add water.
Cook until melted. Set aside.
Heat milk to almost boiling. Beat egg yolks with sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Slowly pour hot milk over caramel syrup. Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Add meringue and brown.

title: sausage rigatoni
directions: Remove casings from sausage, crumble meat.
In a deep heavy frying pan over medium-low heat, melt butter, add sausage, onion and cook slowly, stirring occasionally until sausage is lightly browned.
Meanwhile cook rigatoni in boiling salted water until al dente; drain well.	Saute garlic in small saucepan with oil until golden.
Add garlic and thinly sliced radicchio if available, cream and wine to sausage and onions.
(Don't get too hot or it will curdle cream.)
Increase heat to medium-high and bring to a boil.
Adjust so mixture boils gently, stirring occasionally until sauce thickens (approx. 5 minutes)	Mix in the drained rigatoni with the grated Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle a little ground nutmeg for a great flavor.
Serve with additional grated Parmesan cheese. Serves 4.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: If mushrooms are very small, leave on stems; if large, remove stems and save for some other dish. Cook mushrooms in boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain well.

title: marsha's wedding punch
directions: Mix orange juice, pineapple juice, lemonade and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add ginger ale.
Add a little water, if necessary.
For peach colored punch, put in 1 package of cherry Kool-Aid and 1/2 medium can of maraschino cherries.
For red punch, use 2 packages cherry Kool-Aid and 1 can maraschino cherries.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour until bubbly.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, sherry and Mozzarella cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat, stir in parsley, onion and crabmeat.
Pour into quiche dish or other shallow dish.
Heat in microwave or oven.
Then lightly brown under broiler.
Serve with crackers or bagel chips.

title: spinach dip
directions: Let spinach thaw and squeeze out water very well.
Combine remaining ingredients, then add spinach and chill.
(Let set about 3 hours, until soup mix has a chance to soften.)
Good with chips or vegetables.

title: spicy chicken casserole
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil. Place over medium high heat until hot.
Add chicken.
Cook 5 minutes or until lightly brown.
Combine chicken, corn, onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, salsa, cilantro, chili powder and jalapenos in a large bowl; stir well.

title: date-nut loaf
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add soda to finely cut dates.
Add boiling water.
Sift flour and salt. Slowly add creamed mixture to dates, then slowly add flour and salt.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan (or oil and line with waxed paper) for 1 hour or more, until toothpick inserted into center comes out dry at 350°.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Put 1/2 rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolks and 3/4 cup sugar.
Put on top of rolls next apple pie filling, the rest of rolls.
Brush with egg white.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: hobo beans
directions: Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir at least twice.

title: baked rice
directions: Brown
onion in butter and add to remaining ingredients in covered casserole.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole(my christmas eve dish)
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Add canned tomatoes, crushing them or quartering them.
Add sliced okra; cook until slimy (I like to use frozen okra).
Add peeled and deveined shrimp, cooking only until pink.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: carolina barbecue
directions: Randomly pierce the surface of the roast with a sharp knife. In a Dutch oven, brown roast on all sides in hot oil.
In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour sauce over roast and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours or until pork is tender.
Baste roast with sauce during cooking time.
Remove pork from oven, cool and slice.
Serves 20.

title: cheddar parmesan potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt 4 Tbsp. butter over low heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk, cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in salt and cheeses until melted.
Add potatoes, stir gently to mix.
Place in a greased 2 qt. baking dish.
Melt the remaining butter, toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend cream cheese and butter together. Add vanilla and sugar; mix well.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, 1/2 cup water and seasonings.
Shape into balls.
Place on baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: egg nog chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add hot water slowly.
Cook in double boiler until custard, stir constantly. Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add small amounts of hot custard, then dissolve all in hot custard.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add rum and nutmeg.
Stir into stiffly beaten egg whites to which remaining sugar has been added. Pour into baked shell.
Garnish with whipped cream and nutmeg.

title: buckeyes(chocolate covered peanut butter balls)
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter and peanut butter until well blended and chill.
Melt chocolate chips, butter (2 tablespoons) and paraffin.
Form peanut butter mixture into little balls, dip with toothpick into melted chocolate mixture and place on wax paper until set.

title: prosciutto (or ham) wraps
directions: Cut each melon half into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Half slices to make 2 to 2 1/2-inch long slices.
Wrap Prosciutto slice or ham around each piece of melon.
Tie with green onion strip.
Makes about 4 dozen wraps.

title: roast beef
directions: Allow 10 minutes per pound, plus extra 10 minutes for well done roast.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Put mixture in pan and bake at 360° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate-vanilla dessert
directions: Mix together and crumble in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: one dish beef dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion. Stir in salt and pepper, soup and corn; bring to boil. Pour into 8-inch dish. Put biscuits on top. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: "almond crunch cake"
directions: Mix white cake mix according to package directions.
Add 1 teaspoon almond flavoring to the batter.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch sheet pan.
Remove cake from oven.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Break up cauliflower into small pieces and cook in water until tender.
Add veggies to cauliflower halfway through cooking. Drain all veggies.
Heat over low temperature milk, soup and cheese.
Add cooked veggies to liquid mix and simmer until ready to serve, stirring frequently.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick banana muffins
directions: Cream ingredients together in the order given. Bake 12-15 minutes at 400° in greased 2-inch muffin tins, or use baking cups. Makes 12-24 muffins.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325°.

title: maque choux(smothered corn)
directions: Remove corn from cob, cutting 2/3 of the way to the cob. Scrape the cob with the dull edge of a knife.
You should have 4 cups corn mixture. Set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, cook onion and green pepper in margarine about 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in corn, tomato, salt and red and black peppers.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until corn is tender.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Sift together dry ingredients and add to oil mixture.
Beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Add grated carrots and nuts.
Spread into pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger (turkey) soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour or until veggies are done.
Serving size:
1 cup = 155.5 calories.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Chop pecans, candied cherries and pineapple into medium pieces; dredge with a small amount of flour.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add well-beaten eggs and blend well.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder; fold into egg and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; mix well.
Add fruits and nuts, blending well.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Line with heavy brown paper and grease again.
Pour batter into pan. Place in cold oven, turn temperature to 250° and bake 3 hours. Cool in pan on cake rack before turning out.
Remove liner.
Store in a cook, dark place.

title: cheese-tomato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice tomatoes into fourths; sprinkle with sugar and pepper.
In bowl, toss together cheese, celery and onion.
Place half of the tomato slices into a greased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle on half of the cheese mixture over tomato slices.
Repeat layers.
Toss crumbs with butter; sprinkle over casserole mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken in 3 cups of water with carrot, sliced onion and celery and leaves.
At the end of the first hour of cooking, add 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon paprika or 3 or 4 peppercorns. Cook pasta; drain.
Add the sauteed sliced mushrooms.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Skillet may be rubbed with a clove of garlic.
Make a sauce with butter or your choice of 2 tablespoons flour and 2 cups chicken broth.
Remove from stove. Add 1 cup heated (not boiled) heavy cream and the sherry.

title: ham and cauliflower casserole
directions: Divide cauliflower into separate flowerets. Parboil 8 minutes or until almost tender. Mix cauliflower with crumbs; add ham, cheese and green pepper. Place in casserole. Spread sour cream over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and nuts in bowl.
In saucepan, mix oleo, Coke and cocoa.
Bring to boil.
Add marshmallows.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Add sugar and flour mixture. Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients together and put in a large casserole.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 2 hours.

title: makes-its-own crust custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in blender for 30 seconds. Pour into a well-greased and floured 9-inch glass pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Pie will rise, but will settle as it cools and will form a light crust.

title: hot chili dip
directions: In medium skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Blend in Lipton California dip, chili sauce and chili powder.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: chocolate chip cookies from hillary
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat together the shortening, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs, beating until fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats.
Stir in chips.
Drop teaspoonfuls of batter onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool cookies on sheets for 2 minutes before placing them on wire rack for further cooling.
Yields 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: popsicles deluxe(these are not only good, but there is less drip.)
directions: Mix well; add 2 cups cold water.
Stir and pour into popsicle containers.

title: spaghetti with tuna
directions: Fry chunks of washed tuna in olive oil until a little brown. Remove.
In same pan, saute chopped green onions and sliced mushrooms.
In large pot, combine spaghetti sauce, crushed tomatoes, garlic cloves, whole onion, parsley, basil and sauteed green onions and mushrooms.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add fried tuna and cook additional 20 minutes.
Remove whole onion, garlic cloves and basil leaves.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
(Shop 'n Save carries Antolino brand.)

title: toffee pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Stir in sugar, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons instant coffee.
Cook until thick; chill. Fill shell with ice cream; spread chocolate sauce on top.
Spoon on cream which has been whipped with sugar, vanilla and coffee. Freeze and top with chocolate curls.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Stir in peanut butter, then stir in other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add baking powder and flour, alternating with milk.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook in boiling salted water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and mash.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Cook the Karo syrup and sugar over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add the peanut butter; melt.
Add the Rice Krispies; stir.
When all cereal is coated, press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and the butterscotch chips; spread over Rice Krispies.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma peggy's angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Sift flour and 3/4 cup sugar together three times. Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar in large bowl at highest speed until light and fluffy. Sprinkle remaining sugar over egg whites, two tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition. Continue beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in extracts.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Thaw potatoes for 1/2 hour.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together all ingredients and pour milk on top.
Put on shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all together, except chocolate chips;
beat.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes in a Bundt pan. Good with or without icing.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix applesauce and raisins; set aside.
Combine sugar, egg and shortening in mixing bowl; beat until fluffy.
Stir in applesauce and raisins.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder, soda and spices.
Add and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop soft dough onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
They will be soft cookies.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients to your taste.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla and flour.
Bake at 350°.
Toothpick comes clean when done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar and beat in eggs.
Add vanilla. Beat more.
Sift flour with cocoa; add vinegar to milk.
Alternate with flour to batter.
Beat well.
Pour into 2 to 3 (9-inch) layer pans or sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, depending on oven.
Top with Red Velvet Frosting.

title: drop pecan crispies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, oleo and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift and blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan. Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add vanilla and stir in.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add.
Mix.
Stir in the apple and walnuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be served plain, with powdered sugar or whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and chill.
Take out of refrigerator and roll in pecans.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit, nuts and peel and dredge in 1/2 cup of the flour. Sift remaining flour with dry ingredients.
Cream butter; add sugar and honey and stir in well beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients and juice alternately.
Pour batter over floured fruit and mix thoroughly.
Bake in a slow oven for 4 hours at 300° in greased pan.
Put 2 cups of water in a pan in the oven while cake is cooking.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins, pineapple and nuts; blend.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 long pans at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
(Or if using loaf pans, bake 1 hour.)

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Use 2 pots.
In one pot, boil noodles until done and strain. In the other pot, melt butter.
Add frozen seasoning mix.
Saute until tender and clear.
On medium heat, add half and half milk. Add Cheez Whiz.
When cheese is melted, add crawfish or shrimp. Season to taste.
Allow to cook approximately 20 minutes.
Mix noodles and sauce.
Put into casserole dish.
Serves 6 to 8. Sprinkle Italian bread crumbs on top when done, adds good taste.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add eggs, buttermilk, shortening and vanilla to dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to mix up.
Cover; store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Will keep up to 5 to 6 weeks.
Grease muffin tins to bake. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: long island tea
directions: Mix in big glass with ice and add Coke.

title: big mama's chocolate pie
directions: Brown pie crust.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and butter.
Add just enough hot water to mix.
Mix well, then add milk, yolks and vanilla.
Cook on top of stove until thick.
Pour into browned pie crust.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Pare and core apples without cutting through the stem end. In a saucepan, stir sugar, water and cinnamon until blended.
Heat over low heat.
When mixture is warm, add apples, one at a time. Simmer until fruit is tender, then remove apples from syrup. Place apples in serving dish and pour syrup over them if desired.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well beaten eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Crumble sausage in large frying pan. Cook and drain fat off. Add green pepper, onion and garlic. Cook 5 minutes and stir. Together add tomatoes and seasonings.
Pour in black-eyed peas with the liquid in can. Cover and simmer, slowly 15 minutes. Serve hot with cheese on top.

title: finger drumsticks
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips.
Divide each wing by cutting through joint with a sharp knife.
Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour bouillon over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or until tender.
Drain.
Place on broiler pan.

title: crunchy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam celery in a small amount of salted water until tender but still crisp, about 5 minutes.
Drain well. Add water chestnuts, basil, garlic and soup.
Stir.
Pour into a well-greased 2 quart casserole.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce, using 1/4 cup water to rinse cans. Add spices and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Cook macaroni per directions on box.
Add to beef mixture.
Put half of beef and macaroni mixture in a greased casserole dish. Layer cheese on top and add rest of beef and macaroni. Top with pepperoni. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: shredded beef sandwich
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Place in a 4-quart slow cooker (crock-pot).
Combine other ingredients and place over meat. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.
Remove meat and shred with fork.
Discard fat and any bones.
Strain meat juices.
Skim off fat.
Can return juices and meat back into slow cooker until ready to serve.
Spoon meat into semi-hard rolls.
Use any remaining juice for dipping.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Into large bowl measure all ingredients except chips.
Mix with an electric mixer on medium speed, scraping side occasionally.
Add chips; stir well. Form 1-inch balls of cookie dough; place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes, or until lightly browned around edges. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare bottom crust.
Toss apples and orange juice in a large bowl.
Combine light brown sugar, granulated sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Toss with apples until coated.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Moisten pastry edge with water.
Cover with top crust.
Brush top with milk.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon granulated sugar.
Cover top with sheet of foil to prevent overbrowning.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil. Bake 10 to 20 minutes longer or until apples are tender, filling in center is bubbling and crust is golden brown.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix all together and put into a casserole or a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle some low-fat or fat-free Mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with a salad (fat-free dressing) and bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In casserole lay chicken (cut in strips).
Cover with cheese slices.
Mix milk and soup together and pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix in stuffing mix.
Sprinkle stuffing over casserole.
Start in cold oven and bake at 350° covered for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler or microwave.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and brandy until smooth.
Add chocolate chips and eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream; mix until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack for 30 minutes.

title: waikiki coconut cream pie
directions: Scald the milk. Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt and gradually add to the milk, stirring constantly, until smooth. Cook slowly in top of double boiler, stirring constantly, until it begins to thicken. Beat egg yolks and slowly beat in a few spoonfuls of the hot mixture. Slowly add to the cooking milk mixture.
Continue cooking until thick and smooth.
Cool slightly. Add vanilla and pour into crust.
Whip the cream until stiff and add a few spoonfuls of sugar.
Spread over the pie and sprinkle with the coconut.

title: cajun crab dip
directions: Saute onion and butter until tender.
Add soup, pimento, mustard and parsley and bring to boil.
Add crab and shrimp and simmer 5 minutes.

title: parslied chicken bake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in plastic bag.
Shake to mix. Place 2 pieces of chicken in bag.
Shake to coat.
Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil water.
Stir in macaroni.
Boil rapidly, stirring occasionally, 7 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well. Return to pan.
Add Parkay spread stick and milk and cheese mix. Mix well.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: fried apples
directions: Peel the apples; cut into eighths and remove core.
Heat 5 tablespoons butter in a heavy skillet.
Add apples and saut; stir gently over medium heat, about 15 minutes, until just starting to be tender to the fork.
Add more butter only if needed.
Sprinkle the lemon juice over apples and then add the sugar.
Stir once and cover with heavy lid; turn off the heat and let stand covered for 15 minutes.
Apples should maintain shape and some texture.
Serve with pork chops or chicken.
Yields 6 servings.

title: butter crusted chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika in melted oleo.
Coat each piece of chicken with the mixture by brushing it on.
Place in foil-lined pan and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for an additional hour.

title: butterscotch crunchies(hay stacks)
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot, not boiling, water in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let sit about 30 minutes.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in bowl.
Blend well and set aside.
Put half of batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with meat, onion, peppers and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon flop cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, then add flour and baking powder. Add hot milk and butter.
Put butter in milk and heat in microwave.
Bake at 350 degrees.
Take from oven and spread generously with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: cheese pasta casserole
directions: *See recipe for sauce under Sauce Section.

title: glogg
directions: Boil the spices with the water in a pan under lid on low heat for about 30 minutes.
Pour liquid through a strainer.
Mix with wine and sugar.
If desired, add about 1 dl (2/5 cup) vodka or brandy to make the glogg stronger.
Serve the glogg hot (don't let it boil) in small cups or glasses.
Traditional condiments are peeled almonds and raisins that you put into the glogg.

title: barbecue beef on buns
directions: In large skillet, melt oleo; add beef.
Cook, breaking up meat until browned.
Stir in catsup, water, lemon juice, celery, onions, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until celery and onions are tender.
Serve with carrot sticks, potato chips and olives.

title: egg-lemon soup(greek soup)
directions: Bring stock to a boil.
Add rice and simmer over low heat until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Prepare egg-lemon sauce.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add yolks, one at a time.
Continue beating.
Beat in lemon juice.
Very gradually add 2 cups of hot broth to egg-lemon mixture, stirring constantly.
(Too much heat and not enough stirring may cause curdling.)
Stir egg mixture into broth; cover and let stand 5 minutes off the heat.
Serve at once.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add soda, salt and 1/2 teaspoon of baking powder and sift.
Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add chocolate and blend.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla.
Turn into two 9-inch pans lined on bottom with foil. Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Spread with icing as desired.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together graham cracker crumbs, artificial sweetener and margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs. Press into bottom of 2 pie shells. This will not completely cover shell. Bake for 5 to 7 minutes. Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Drain zucchini.
Beat eggs well.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla to zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients and add to moist ingredients. Stir until well blended.

title: frozen corn
directions: Cut raw corn off the cob.
Measure and put in a heavy pot; add butter and water.
Start heating on low until butter melts, then increase heat and bring to a slow boil.
Boil 15 minutes. Set off heat and cool by setting pot in ice water or overnight in refrigerator.
When corn is cold, fill freezer boxes and freeze. No salt!

title: broken glass cake
directions: Dissolve each package of gelatin in 1 1/2 cups of hot water. Put in refrigerator trays to set. Bring pineapple juice to a boil and add 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Stir until dissolved.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add hot water to oats and let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Cream together the margarine, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, soda and cinnamon and add to sugar mixture; add oatmeal mixture and blend.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Add topping. Serves 12 to 15.

title: west coast pasta
directions: Saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until mushy.
Add other ingredients and toss with pasta.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
This will keep for several days.

title: slow cooked pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 3 x 1-inch strips; brown in oil in skillet. Transfer to a slow cooker.
Combine the next 7 ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours or until meat is tender.
Add tomatoes and green peppers.
Cook on low for 1 hour longer.

title: praline coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil, sour cream and vanilla. Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer.
Put pecans in food processor.
Take 1/3 of the cake batter and put into a separate bowl.
Add finely ground pecans and brown sugar.
Mix together well.
Pour 1/2 of the remaining cake batter into greased and floured pan.
Cover with pecan-batter mixture.
Pour remaining 1/2 of cake batter on top of pecan-batter mixture.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate, remove cake pan and continue to cool completely on wire rack.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions. Add margarine; stir until melted. Add corn and soup. Add grated cheese (more, if desired). Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and add some more grated cheese on top.

title: pumpkin milk shakes
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed about 15 seconds or until smooth.
Makes 2 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: trifle
directions: Layer as follows: 1/2 cubed cake, pistachio pudding mixed with pineapple with juice (no milk), 1/2 cubed cake, lemon pudding (mixed as directed on box) and strawberries, drained.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: low country boil
directions: Fill soup pot half full of water.
Cut sausage into 2-inch lengths and put into water.
Add Season-All, lemon juice and salt. Cover until water begins to boil.
Break ears of corn in halves and put in boiling water.
Cover and let boil for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and boil for 5 more minutes.
Drain and serve.
Serves 5.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 325° for two hours.

title: gaye's crabmeat triangles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread onto 12 muffin halves. Cut each half into 8 triangles.
Broil at 350° until bubbly.
Can be frozen whole.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In a large bowl, mix remaining flour (2 1/4 cups), sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make dough soft. On floured surface, knead 4 minutes.
On greased baking sheet roll dough to 14
x 10-inch.
Spread dressing down center 1/3 of dough.
Top with beef, cheese and sauerkraut.
Cut 1-inch wide strips along sides of filling out to dough edges.
Alternating sides, fold strips at angle across filling.
Cover loaf and place pan over 1/2 filled shallow pan of boiling water for 15 minutes. Brush with egg white and sprinkle seed.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk.
Let cool a few minutes. Add milk.

title: onion-mushroom rice
directions: Combine and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8.

title: shirley's diabetic chocolate cookie
directions: Note:
Fudge topping sold at the Basket Case, University Mall, Hardy Street, Hattiesburg, Mississippi.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook potatoes.
Cover with butter and sugar.
Beat eggs, add to potato mixture.
Add spice and milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: chicken cazenova
directions: Roll chicken in flour mixed with parsley flakes, salt, pepper, paprika, garlic powder and oregano.
Brown chicken in oil or butter in skillet.
Remove to baking dish.
Add many sliced or canned mushrooms to skillet juices and brown slightly.
Add Marsala wine to mixture.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Slice small package of Mozzarella cheese.
Place on chicken pieces.
Add pimientos on top of each piece.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: susan's pineapple and pudding cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Follow directions on box.
Remove from oven and punch holes in cake with fork.
Mix and bring to boil the pineapple and sugar.
Pour warm mixture over warm cake.
Prepare pudding.
After cool, spread over cake.
When cake is cool, cover with 8 ounces of Cool Whip and coconut.

title: crock-pot mac and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; mix milk and eggs.
Add melted margarine and 2 cups cheese until thoroughly blended.
Add macaroni; stir well and pour into crock-pot.
Pour remaining cheese on top.
Cover and cook for three hours.
Do not remove lid until done.

title: dreamsicle dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
Mix orange sherbet and Cool Whip. Spread on cooled graham crackers.
Freeze.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Combine with pie filling and pineapple. Chill until set. Mix together sour cream, cream cheese, sugar
and
vanilla. Spread over gelatin. Sprinkle with nuts and chill.

title: cornmeal-cranberry and yogurt muffins(makes 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line twelve muffin tins.
Coarsely chop cranberries in processor.
Set aside.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Whisk yogurt, milk, butter and eggs in medium bowl to blend.
Add to dry ingredients; mix just until combined.
Fold in cranberries.
Divide batter equally among muffin cups.
Bake until golden and tester inserted into center comes out clean, about 20 minutes.
Transfer muffins to rack and cool.

title: summer squash relish
directions: Take water, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and turmeric and boil for 10 minutes.
Put in jars, seal and process 10 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight in order for all the flavors to meld together.

title: salmonettes
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Put salmon into a mixing bowl, breaking it apart well with a fork, then add the flour and slightly beaten egg.
Add pepper, if desired, then mix well.
Add the baking powder to the reserved liquid.
Beat well with fork until foamy.
Pour this into the salmon mixture; stir until blended.

title: apricot nut bars
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and peel. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Mix well. Spread dough in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover dough with apricot preserves.
Beat egg whites. Slowly add 1/4 cup sugar, beating well after each addition.
Beat until stiff. Fold in chopped nuts.
Spread over apricot layer. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut in small squares.

title: overnight yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1/2 c. warm water and 1/2 tsp. sugar, set aside for 10 minutes until yeast bubbles.
Mix together with a beater the eggs 1/2 c. sugar, oil and salt.
Add 4 c. warm water, yeast mixture and 8 c. flour, mixing as you go.
Knead until smooth. Cover dough with saran wrap and refrigerate until you use.	Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can be used for bread, dinner rolls or sweet rolls.

title: nachos supreme
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add seasoning according to package directions.
On large platter, spread nacho chips evenly. Sprinkle ground beef on top of chips.
Add toppings on top of ground beef, whichever way you prefer.
Top with salt, pepper and sour cream.

title: snow cream cake
directions: Mix cake following directions on box.
Add 1/2 of 7 ounce can of coconut to batter.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Poke holes in cake while hot, then let cool.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash off the jalapenos and take a knife and make a slit into the top part of it.
Remove seeds; use water to get the rest of seeds out.
(You can also use your finger to make sure all seeds are out.)
Insert a chunk of any type of cheese you want into the jalapeno.
Take Owen's sausage and divide into 10 equal portions.
Wrap a portion of sausage around each jalapeno making sure to cover entirely.
Drop each one into Shake 'n Bake Hot-N-Spicy bag and shake thoroughly coating the sausage.
Remove from the bag.
Place on a foil covered baking pan.	Bake for 1 hour (checking every 15 minutes to rotate jalapenos to ensure even browning) or until sausage is crispy brown.

title: green bean bake
directions: Save small amount of onion rings.
Mix all ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook for 20 minutes at 325°, then place remaining onion rings on top and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: rich peanut butter bars(easy)
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt peanut butter and margarine in bowl over hot water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Place in 1 quart of salted water along with onion, sliced.
Boil until tender.
Reduce to simmer.
Remove 2 cups of water and add milk to potatoes and onion.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Heat until butter is melted and serve.
(This will be thick.)

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a bowl, sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar. Add seeds.
Cut in shortening with pastry cutter or two knives. Pour in buttermilk and raisins.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together gently.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, ginger ale and oil. Blend in walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
This is a green cake and is perfect to serve during the Christmas holidays or for any festive occasion.

title: baked creamed mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until golden.
Combine eggs, crumbs, milk, cream, salt and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; mix well.
Blend in mushrooms and onions.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until golden and set.
Serve with chicken or fish.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in baking dish in the order given.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: crackle-top gingersnaps
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; beat egg and molasses.
Add to cream mixture.
Chill one hour.
Roll into 1 inch balls and dip in granulated sugar to coat.
Space 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When done the cookies will look fluffy and light.
Tops will fall and be crinkly when the air hits them.
Do not overbake.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, soup and cheese in casserole dish. Crumble cornbread over top and dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 400° until brown and bubbly.

title: vickie's chocolate brownie pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, butter, vanilla, flour, chopped nuts and eggs together and pour into pie crusts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: toffee
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Line foil with crackers close as you can.
Melt sugar and butter on stovetop; cook 1 minute to dissolve.
Pour over saltines.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle milk chocolate bits over warm crackers and smear after a couple minutes.
While chocolate is warm sprinkle on nuts. Let cool or place in freezer and break into pieces several hours later.
